msgid "Current Objectives:"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:342
msgid "Move Galas, Elynia and Mal Keshar to Fort Eldáin"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:358
msgid "I don’t like this... There are signs of a recent battle in this area."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:363
msgid "Quickly, let us investigate what happened here. I hope it’s not too late."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Bowman
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:449
msgid "Who are you? Why, do you bring your unholy slaves to feast on the remains of our fallen?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:454
msgid "We are sworn allies of the peoples of the Far North, and the undead support us against our enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Footpad
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:460
msgid "It is... it is the Lady of Light! I had heard rumors but this is..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:465
msgid "This fortress barely stands. What vile creatures have come to plague the northern country?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Bowman
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:471
msgid "The elves, my lady. The elves have gone mad and are attacking each other, laying waste to every settlement in their path. Neither faction is willing to seek a peaceful end to this conflict, and we don’t think we can withstand their siege for much longer. Most of our men have died defending the city walls, and resources are increasingly scarce."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Bowman
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:497
msgid "We cannot continue without help, and the messengers we sent to the Grand Council for reinforcements have not returned yet. I’ll probably hate myself for the rest of my life for asking help from those who deal with dark magic, but..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:503
msgid "Pfft, we cannot waste our time here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:512
msgid "We must help these poor people and try to negotiate a deal with our kinsmen. We must not allow another civil war to tear our civilization apart! Otherwise..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:517
msgid "Our sacrifices would have been in vain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:522
msgid "We’ll help you defend your fortress until those reinforcements arrive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Bowman
#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:528
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:176
msgid "Thank you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Footpad
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:543
msgid "Lead us, my lord."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:612
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:589
msgid "Resist until the Grand Council’s reinforcements arrive at the end of turns"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:618
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:594
msgid "Enemy units capture the town center"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:622
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:598
msgid "The town center is represented by the villages found within four tiles of its keep"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:623
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:599
msgid "You will not be able to recall the human defense in later scenarios"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:614
msgid "Death of an enemy leader"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:638
msgid "Who is it that helps the human sub-people defend their town against the true rulers of the forest?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:643
msgid "I am Galas, an elf of the Valley of Elynia like you. What is the reason for this unnecessary bloodshed?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:648
msgid "We are at war with those who have taken the life of Lord Inodien and his successor! Are you supporters of their foul cause too?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:653
msgid "You know me well, Unidë — I would not support anyone, elf or otherwise, who would threaten the life of our leaders and our civilization. However, you are not doing any good by murdering innocent humans and elves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:658
msgid "There must be a way to solve this problem without resorting to fighting. In these grim times, with war already raging in the outer lands, the last thing we need is conflict between ourselves as well. It will be our definitive doom. The traitors must be judged by elvish law, not by chaos and death."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:663
msgid "Who do you think you are to give me orders? I am in charge of our people now, and I do not listen to those who ally themselves with this worthless human scum and their foul dark sorcerers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:668
msgid "Diplomacy isn’t going to work, of course — this petty elf has a death wish."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:673
msgid "Avoid killing their leaders at all costs. If we want to solve this conflict, we’ll need the Grand Council to negotiate with the faction leaders, and without them, I fear that their successors may incite an even worse bloodshed. I only wish we could stop our kinsmen without resorting to violence."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:678
msgid "As it seems now, there is no other option for us than to hold out against their troops until help arrives. To arms!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:693
msgid "Though our enemies will not die by my hand, my brethren will avenge me! May this be the last day the traitors live to see the light of Naia and Sela!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:705
msgid "We shouldn’t have allowed her to die. Now it will be nigh impossible to put an end to this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Celán
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:719
msgid "Alas, I have fallen before putting an end to this conflict."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:731
msgid "We shouldn’t have allowed him to die. Now it will be nigh impossible to put an end to this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:754
msgid "I die... for our people!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:775
msgid "Ahh, great. Now we are killing other elves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Celán
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:797
msgid "We must take this settlement if we are to have any hope of crushing this rebellion. Onwards!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:805
msgid "Let us see if Galas and the humans will continue to obstruct us once their precious fort has been reduced to ashes!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. Mal Keshar is being sarcastic. He doesn't care.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:811
msgid "Oh no, Galas, this is terrible. We are going to have to turn— kill even more elves. Such a tragedy. How hopeless."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Celán
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:830
msgid "Keep pressing on! We cannot afford to lose this fight!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:838
msgid "The situation is not improving. If those reinforcements don’t arrive soon we won’t be able to hold this place for much longer!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:852
msgid "We need reinforcements, now!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Orcish Slurbow, id=Kar-velgan
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:901
msgid "Kar-velgan"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arnesius
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:926
msgid "Elves, stop this brutal bloodshed! You have slaughtered many innocent northerners; humans, orcs, and elves alike. This dreadful display breaches the treaty we signed with Lord Galas!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:931
msgid "We do not listen to human sub-people!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unarye
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:936
msgid "Then you shall listen to your own authorities. I came as soon as I could to bring order to this chaos. You have not only disobeyed the will of your former leader, Lord Galas; you also ignored the advice and command of Elynia, the Lady of Light herself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Arnesius
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:941
msgid "In light of these events and the terms of the treaty, the Grand Council has decided to banish the elvish kind from the northern country. You shall put an end to your civil war and prepare to leave our territory before five days have passed, or we shall order our own troops to deal with you. We do not want to do this, and you are well aware that you are at a numerical disadvantage."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Celán
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:950
msgid "Did one of your kind kill the puny ‘lord’ of these rebels as part of a ruse to banish us from the forests, then?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kar-velgan
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:955
msgid "Listen, wose-born scum: Inodien was slain by no elf, human or orc!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unarye
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:964
msgid "We have good reasons to think that the Chaos Empire sent forth their mercenaries for the purpose of causing this revolt and sending us all to our doom. But we are not letting that happen, at least not today."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:969
msgid "This is not fair! Why should we pay for crimes committed by outsiders?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kar-velgan
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:974
msgid "Your hands are not clean, elf! How do you even dare to ignore that fact in front of the bearers of the law?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:983
msgid "It is true. We have spilled much elvish blood with this fight. Galas and I shall leave these lands as soon as we can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:988
msgid "But my lady, how? None of this is your fault..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:993
msgid "What? And how are we going to travel to Zocthanol Isle then?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Unidë
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:998
msgid "I swear that my people will never forget this, the most vile of treacheries. I shall withdraw my troops and my people from this accursed country today, but I do intend to return some day to demand proper justice!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Celán
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1003
msgid "If the Lady of Light is willing to depart from these lands to never return because of our own misdeeds, then we shall abandon the country as well. Come with me, men!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1016
msgid "Elynia? Can you tell us your plan?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1021
msgid "There is a port to the west in the Bay of Tirigaz. It’s controlled by orcs, but perhaps we can find a way to bribe them so they lend us ships and provisions. It is the only port that doesn’t belong to the Aragwaithi nowadays."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. Here Mal Keshar is supposed to be about to say something like "this is ridiculous" or such.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1028
msgid "This is— Pah. We shall go to Tirigaz, then. But how will we determine the location of Zocthanol Isle?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1033
msgid "That will be my job to do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1043
msgid "Then... I suppose this is where it ends."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1048
msgid "Are you really sure about this, Igor? I thought you would prefer to live among your people in the west instead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1053
msgid "I mean, yes, being with goblins is great! But I’m scared after what happened — you know, the whole Chaos thing? And it seems like the orc chieftains are still bad at guarding the land from invaders from the south. No, I think I’m done being village goblin. I’m gonna become city goblin now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1058
msgid "Hmph. How would a filthy runt like you survive the perils of civilization, I wonder."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1063
msgid "Hey, I can do artsy stuff! Haven’t you heard me sing before? Ahem—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1068
msgid "If I have to listen to that again, I swear to the Dark Gods—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1073
msgid "It has been a long journey for you, and we certainly cannot force you to stick around considering all the dangers that await us next. I just hope we will get to see each other again some day. I think I speak for all three of us when I say we are deeply grateful for your help and support, even through the most nightmarish of circumstances."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1078
msgid "We will miss you greatly. Best of luck, my friend."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1083
msgid "Awww, you guys, I’m tearing up... I will miss you too!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/03_Civil_War.cfg:1088
msgid "Can we just... please. Let us move on already."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:113
msgid "Terror at Dusk"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: id=Darglen, type=Chaos Lorekeeper
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:128
msgid "Darglen"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:190
msgid "That is the sound of those blasted creatures!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:199
msgid "Um... that’s unusual. Could they be behind the death of Inodien? But then..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:204
msgid "... The Chaos Empire must not be in disarray as we thought."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:209
msgid "They shall pay for the senseless destruction and bloodshed they caused. Let us get rid of them before they bring more strife to this country!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:224
msgid "Don’t die yet, vermin! We want some answers before crushing your useless skull against the rocks!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Darglen
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:229
msgid "... And do you really believe I would speak? Heh... you can torture me as much as you want, but you won’t get anything from me!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:234
msgid "Stupid..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:239
msgid "Let him."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:255
msgid "That bastard... Hekuba... He and the Iron Triad must be behind this. But what are they trying to accomplish?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:260
msgid "They want to take revenge on us and our kind after Argan’s death, of course. It seems that as long as their cult exists, so will the Chaos Empire."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:279
msgid "This was the last one, and it doesn’t seem like there are any more groups coming here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:284
msgid "Let’s not worry a lot about them. These pathetic weaklings are nothing compared to the hordes we fought before."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:289
msgid "Let’s proceed to Tirigaz now, quickly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:294
msgid "Why don’t we go after their leaders and put an end to this stupid war <i>now</i>?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:299
msgid "No... That would be a highly reckless choice. We don’t know what kind of enemies we might be facing other than Mal Hekuba — you have not forgotten our last encounter with him, have you? We are at a disadvantage without more information about them — their leaders, their weapons, their plans. This is why we must find Zocthanol first."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:304
msgid "<i>(sighs)</i> Very well, then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:313
msgid "We have wasted far too much time dealing with these pests. Look! A large swarm is approaching from the south!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/04_Terror_at_Dusk.cfg:318
msgid "Indeed. This... this was not a very prudent idea."
msgstr ""

