#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:552
msgid "170 gold! It seems it was a trading ship!"
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:553
msgid "You retrieve 170 pieces of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:557
msgid "Bah, only 25 pieces of gold. Better than nothing, I guess."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:558
msgid "You retrieve 25 pieces of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:562
msgid "Two pieces of gold? Damn, this must be a joke!"
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:563
msgid "You retrieve two pieces of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:567
msgid "Well, well, 50 pieces of gold can be put to good use!"
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:568
msgid "You retrieve 50 pieces of gold."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#. The pointy-eared demons here are the elves.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:657
msgid "You filthy soft-skinned beasts, this is your last opportunity to return our swamps! We are not planning to retreat to the forests of the pointy-eared demons!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Vatar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:662
msgid "We care nothing for your stupid conflicts on the eastern borders. You trespassed our frontiers and broke our treaty, and now you ask from us the very lands you took by force; after raiding our southern garrison, no less! If you believe we will accede now—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:667
msgid "To the Dark Gods with you and your treaty! The words of an orc are no more meaningful than his fetid breath! Maybe you’ll admit your defeat once we have razed every single one of your precious buildings to the ground. Go ahead, Rishix! Teach them a lesson!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Rishix
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:672
msgid "We’ll make these puny dirt-dwellers rue the day they were born!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:729
msgid "That city to the northwest... is it the port of Tirigaz?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:734
msgid "Yes... it wasn’t so well fortified during my time. So many things have changed since then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#. "Is that smoke I smell?"
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:740
msgid "Is that smoke I— Wait, I hear steps..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Orcish Crossbowman, id=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:757
msgid "Vuruk"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:774
msgid "Hello, strangers! Are you loyal to the Grand Council?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:779
msgid "Ehm..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:784
msgid "Yes, we are."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:789
msgid "Those vile saurians hold the port of Tirigaz under siege, leaving me unable to reach the city to deliver some important news to our lord. I think I speak for all of us when I say that your help would be very appreciated. I need to get to the city keep, but the journey across isn’t safe while those vermin roam about our lands!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:794
msgid "The enemies of our friends are our enemies. We can help you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:799
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) I am curious about their motives... Don’t you think your trust in the orcs could be misplaced?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:804
msgid "We must stop and repel those saurians before they take over Tirigaz or the northern town that provides resources to the port."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:815
msgid "Vuruk, what is it that you need to report to the lord of Tirigaz?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:820
msgid "Hmm... I fear it is nothing I’m allowed to share with anyone but Lord Tan-Vatar and his trusted commanders, at least not at this time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:825
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:371
msgid "Fair enough."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:841
msgid "Come in aid of your kin, friends from the deep sea!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:891
msgid "Ah, ha, ha, hah! They have the support of some wild creatures from the ocean! Nothing we cannot handle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:955
msgid "Where did all these damned creatures come from?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:964
msgid "This is turning out to be much harder than we expected..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1036
msgid "Arthol is being ransacked by the saurians! Now there’s no hope for Tirigaz!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1057
msgid "Tirigaz has been captured! Our mission has failed, and we won’t be able to reach Zocthanol now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1086
msgid "No! I’ve got to... uuugh..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1098
msgid "We let the orcish messenger perish on the battlefield! The lord of Tirigaz is not going to like this..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1113
msgid "The treacherous ones cannot win! Eeaack..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1137
msgid "Damn you, dirt-dwellers!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1162
msgid "I have been struck down by the damned minions of a lich! This is not fair!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1181
msgid "Accursed lich! May the Dark Gods smite you down for this atrocity— Eaugh!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1200
msgid "Noooooo! You’ll suffer for this atrocity!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1220
msgid "Ha, ha, ha! Die, fool!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1225
msgid "No! The city will fall... without my leadership... *ack*"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1230
msgid "Take that, orcish scum! Your leader is dead now, and your city is ours!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1242
msgid "The commander of the defense of Tirigaz has been slain! The city won’t resist for much longer now..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1264
msgid "Don’t get any closer to our villages, you vermin!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ishkaal
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1269
msgid "Crush their villages into the ground!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1303
msgid "These villages belong to the lord of Tirigaz! We must protect them, not capture them!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1322
msgid ""
"The fountain’s water is overflowing with an unusual energy.\n"
"\n"
"You catch a glimpse of a strange-looking faerie observing you from behind a nearby tree, but by the time you approach it she has seemingly vanished. In the hurry to return to the fray you almost slip on a puddle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1333
msgid "The fountain’s water continues to overflow with an unusual energy."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1357
msgid "(<i>jumps in</i>) Wheeeeeeee!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1408
msgid "Shimmering Fountain"
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1411
msgid "The Naiad’s spell blesses anyone who takes a swim in the water of this fountain with newfound vim and courage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Orcish Warrior, id=Vitork
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1438
msgid "Vitork"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1449
msgid "Yes! We did it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Vatar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1454
msgid "This is an important battle you’ve helped us win, travelers. The city of Tirigaz shall be eternally thankful for your assistance."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1459
msgid "It is our duty to assist our allies in these times. However, I believe this soldier has something to tell you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vitork
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1464
msgid "Vuruk, brother, you made it! Did you discover anything new?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vuruk
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1469
msgid "Ha, indeed! I need to talk with you about it later, but now I must report to the chieftains."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Vatar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1474
msgid "I see you helped Vuruk return home safe and sound. Well done! So, what can we do for you to repay our debt?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1479
msgid "Um, we are currently looking for transportation services. We must sail the open ocean to find a certain island..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Vatar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1484
msgid "I mean no offense, but only fools would dare sail the <i>open ocean</i>! Nobody has ventured into farther waters and returned in one piece, ever! Nobody knows exactly what kind of creatures inhabit the Vast Sea! Nobody knows for certain what lies beyond the horizon, but it surely can’t be good, you see! Why would anyone want to travel so far into unknown waters, when there are plenty of safer unexplored lands awaiting back whence you came?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1489
msgid "We have a mission to complete, but much like Vuruk’s, it is not something we should discuss with..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1494
msgid "We know the location of a certain isle where some people who once lived on the Great Continent went to. We need to gather some information from them — as part of a mission for the Grand Council."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1499
msgid "Uh, huh."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Tan-Vatar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/05_Bay_of_Tirigaz.cfg:1504
msgid "The Grand Council? Why didn’t you say so in the first place! We’ll do anything we can to help you in your mission. It’ll be difficult to gather an appropriate crew for you, but at least I can give you one of our fastest transport vessels."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:146
msgid "Quenoth Isle"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#. [side]: id=Gaellis, type=Quenoth Champion
#. [side]: id=Maina, type=Quenoth Sun Sylph
#. [side]: id=Inara, type=Quenoth Ranger, gender=female
#. [side]: id=Lintaen, type=Quenoth Hero
#. [side]: id=Listra, type=Quenoth Sun Singer
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:46
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:50
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:91
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:150
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:196
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:267
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:45
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:63
msgid "team_name^Quenoth"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:110
msgid "This place appears to be abandoned... Are you sure this is the correct island?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:115
msgid "Not completely... but it’s possible that the Quenoth elves just avoid these shores for some reason."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:120
msgid "Let’s explore and try to find them, then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:261
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1359
msgid "Time passes..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:293
msgid "Maybe we should return to the ship. I’m not really sure about going into the forest at night, it could be dangerous."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:298
msgid "Why are you hesitating now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:305
msgid "Do you remember when we almost lost you in the caves beneath Wesmere? I don’t want to risk that occurring again. We don’t know why we haven’t found any elves here and..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:316
msgid "Is there something you haven’t told me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:321
msgid "Galas, I—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:332
msgid "I hear movement among the trees."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Nion, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Valad, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Hara, type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Yon, type=Quenoth Scout, id=Ladien
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:345
msgid "Nion"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Nion, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Valad, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Hara, type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Yon, type=Quenoth Scout, id=Ladien
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:357
msgid "Valad"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Nion, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Valad, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Hara, type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Yon, type=Quenoth Scout, id=Ladien
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:367
msgid "Hara"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Nion, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Valad, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Hara, type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Yon, type=Quenoth Scout, id=Ladien
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:385
msgid "Yon"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Nion, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Valad, type=Quenoth Flanker, id=Hara, type=Quenoth Fighter, id=Yon, type=Quenoth Scout, id=Ladien
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:395
msgid "Ladien"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:409
msgid "Who are you and where do you come from? You don’t seem to be of our kin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:414
msgid "We are elves! There’s no need to point at us with those arrows and swords, either; we’re clearly at a disadvantage here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:419
msgid "You do not look or dress like our people. Is this some kind of joke? We are pretty sure we’ve never seen your faces on this island."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Hara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:424
msgid "They are probably impostors sent by Uria to destroy our home!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:429
msgid "Let us explain..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:434
msgid "Seize them!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:441
msgid "Stop!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:457
msgid "(<i>spreading her wings</i>) How can you <b>not</b> recognize your kin, young girl? Have the Quenoth elves truly forgotten their origins?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:468
msgid "(<i>in a calm, sad tone</i>) When did you last see the essence of the forest blazing in the dark?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:524
msgid "Elynia held a small fire in her hands, illuminating the surroundings with a strong, azure light. The elves stared in awe at her subtle but effective display of the power of Faerie; some of them stepped back, alarmed, uncertain of what to make of the unusual situation."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_01_Quenoth_Isle.cfg:554
msgid "Come with me."
msgstr ""

