msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Leria, type=Tauroch Stalwart
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:374
msgid "Leria"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:428
msgid "Lord Gaellis, son of Kalehssar, we found these two strangers on the southeastern shores. They came from the northern seas, and seem to bring the light of Eloh with them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:439
msgid "Eloh? That name..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:444
msgid "No land dwellers have set foot on this island for a long time. The last recorded landing was centuries ago, when our own kin came here seeking a new home; they made sure no-one was left behind on the continent. Tell us, who are you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:449
msgid "Sir, I am Galas, son of Valthir, and this is..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:454
msgid "Elynia, daughter of Delanith-Isáwen."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:459
msgid "You bear a strong resemblance to us. Spread your wings, Elynia. Albeit unusually pale, your face is that of an elf; but your clothes, and your wings... they are very unlike our own. Where do you come from?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:464
msgid "From the Great Continent — from the region we call the Far North, beyond the tall Heart Mountains that grasp the sky and guard the green lands. There, the suns’ light has not been enough to burn those beautiful forests forever. We are different to you, indeed; we are forest elves, and we have come to seek your help against the great evil that has befallen Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:469
msgid "Forest elves? How is that possible? The last our people saw of the Great Continent were vast deserts plagued with foul orcs, necromancers, and human barbarians. There’s no green life left on it anymore!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:474
msgid "Maybe your people didn’t travel far enough! Most of the central region fits your description, but there are a few secluded valleys where life has continued to thrive, and the Far North is vast enough to allow both humans and orcs to live relatively at peace with each other."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:479
msgid "That is—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Inara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:484
msgid "Kalehssar, the Blade of Eloh, destroyed the dark force that once reigned over Irdya and attempted to erase the last remnants of our kind. What new foe threatens to put an end to our peace now, daughter of the forests?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:489
msgid "The creature slain by his hand was but a servant of a far greater power. The fight is not over yet, and although we have recently vanquished another... minion of hers, the influence she exerts on this world remains as strong as ever."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:500
msgid "I realize that this may sound overly dramatic, but I speak the truth, for I am the slayer of Zhangor, and Eloh guided me back to you in this era because you have the missing page of our civilization’s history: Kalehssar fought Yechnagoth, the Eater of Souls, and defeated her on this island nearly four centuries ago. The enemy we face now is none other than Uria, who has amassed an empire of human followers on the Great Continent. Even now as we speak, they work with the forces of Inferno and their unspeakable creations to destroy all that is left in the world!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:511
msgid "The elves were left aghast by the mention of the three accursed names. They eyed each other nervously, as though they feared that rocks would fall from the sky in response to the bold revelation."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:521
msgid "I cannot do miracles. If you need more proof of our claims—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:526
msgid "At the end of the previous era, you were sent by Eloh to protect elvenkind from the Demon Lord. Now, you have returned to us to protect all Irdya from the Fallen Goddess... Elynia, the power you wield has not been seen by our kin for eons, as much of our forefathers’ knowledge perished with them when the spawn of Uria destroyed their forests. You are a rare gem among the entire elvish civilization, and we have no reason to distrust you. We listen to the call of our forest ancestors, and we agree to help you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:531
msgid "Don’t we all?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:540
msgid "What kind of help do you need?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:545
msgid "Necromancy is the least of evils now that Uria’s minions plague the Great Continent. In our long journey to this island, we have not only been assisted by the orcs of the Far North, but also by a lich who helped us defeat the Chaos Emperor. We will need his help here, so I request that we are allowed to bring our orcish and undead allies to this island."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#. "Why we can’t accede."
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:562
msgid "<i>(nervously)</i> That request... is very... <i>improper</i> for an elf, to say the least... You surely understand why we can’t—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:567
msgid "It is true that many necromancers have worked together with Uria’s minions to bring doom to the natural inhabitants of the continent, including your own ancestors. But it’s also true that knowing whether a creature walks the path of Light or the path of Darkness does not suffice to distinguish evil from good. As for the orcs, they have been our allies even in the past, back when there was only one sun and all elves lived in the forests of Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:572
msgid "We shall allow the orcs and the undead to come to assist you once you tell us exactly what you are going to do, but beware that our warriors and priests are ready to take care of them should they do anything suspicious."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/06_02_Elves_of_a_Different_Land.cfg:577
msgid "We require access to the place where Yechnagoth was destroyed."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: race=bats, type=Water Serpent, race=verlissh
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:179
msgid "The Search for the Past"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#. [side]: type=Shadow Jumping Spider
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:52
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:67
msgid "team_name^Cave Creatures"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:103
msgid "team_name^Yechnagoth’s Guards"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:119
msgid "team_name^Chaos Guards"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:207
msgid "Follow the path and explore underground"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. [else]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:212
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1152
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:99
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:252
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/10_Tears.cfg:212
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/10_Tears.cfg:352
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/11_Ambush_at_the_Gates.cfg:275
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/03_Amidst_the_Ruins_of_Glamdrol.cfg:548
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:680
msgid "Death of Horo"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. [else]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:213
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1153
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:100
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:253
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/10_Tears.cfg:213
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/10_Tears.cfg:353
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/11_Ambush_at_the_Gates.cfg:276
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/03_Amidst_the_Ruins_of_Glamdrol.cfg:549
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:681
msgid "Death of Kyara"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:385
msgid "I don’t like this place. It feels as if something is waiting to ambush us in the darkness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:390
msgid "Heh, darkness. These elves aren’t very smart after all. Why would they think that sending one of their sun-loving youths would be of any help to us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:395
msgid "Keep your mouth shut, decrepit lich! We are being <i>far</i> more lenient than anyone would be with those who deal with your unnatural minions and these filthy apes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:400
msgid "Who are you calling “filthy apes”, you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:405
msgid "Calm down, everyone! If we are to explore these caverns, we’ll need to stay together."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:410
msgid "What are you looking for? Some kind of artifact? Rocks? Spiders?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:415
msgid "We believe these caves beneath the dark citadel may have once been used by our enemies. If that is the case, they may have left behind scrolls, artifacts, or anything else that could provide us with hints."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:420
msgid "This is no time to fight amongst ourselves. Just stay alert and let us see what we can find."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:425
msgid "We will help you as best we can, elf."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:498
msgid "Hmmm, at first glance this seems like a dead end, but those rocks over there seem like they might be concealing something. Galas, I believe we should have some explosives to spare still?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:503
msgid "What’s left should be more than enough to clear the rubble out of the way, but are you sure this isn’t horribly unsafe?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:508
msgid "These tunnels seem very well built and have withstood the passage of time for centuries. I reckon it will take more than a few explosions to bring the ceiling down on us."
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_mining_charge_help
#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_help
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:513
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1317
msgid "Help: Using Charges"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=wme_mining_charge_help
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:535
msgid ""
"In this scenario, you will come across special marked locations where explosives can be set off in order to clear obstructions. Move <b>Galas</b>, <b>Elynia</b>, <b>Mal Keshar</b>, <b>Horo</b>, or <b>Kyara</b> to these locations in order to prime a barrel of explosives which will detonate at the start of next turn.\n"
"\n"
"Beware that the ensuing explosion will <b>kill</b> any units within a one-hex radius, so you must ensure your unit has enough movement points left to move to a safe spot before deploying."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:578
msgid "All set. Clear the area!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=$random
#. [message]: race=human,orc,wolf,goblin,faerie,elf
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:598
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1682
msgid "Fire in the hole!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Death Knight, id=Firden
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:710
msgid "Firden"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:732
msgid "<i>Hissssssss</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:737
msgid "A giant spider. Just a bothersome giant spider."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:756
msgid "Look out, there are undead sentinels standing in our way!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:761
msgid "This is impossible! Our druids purged any evil creatures left on this island after Kalehssar’s victory!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:766
msgid "Above the surface, they might have been unable to detect these slumbering minions. Yes, it appears our presence is what has awakened them after so long."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:782
msgid "There was very little strength left in this guardian. I wonder who was the master of these minions before the place was abandoned?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:787
msgid "Argan, of course. There’s no doubt about it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:809
msgid "Not bad for a sun-loving little girl."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:814
msgid "Shut up, necromancer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:856
msgid "Another dead end. Now what?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:861
msgid "If our past experiences with this sort of construction are anything to go by, this is most likely not the dead end it appears to be. Let us check the small cave to the east."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:897
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3657
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1127
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1345
msgid "Touchplate triggered. A wall moves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:917
msgid ""
"ER█OR: Object connec█ion failed██status code: 0xC000023C█\n"
"\n"
"Acce█s denied."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:934
msgid "What is this?? Why isn’t this damned contraption working? Oh well, I suppose this place has been left unattended for a <b>very</b> long time. No matter, we should be able to blast that brick wall open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:939
msgid "Actually, no... we don’t know exactly how thick it is, and we barely have any explosives left. We would have to head back to the surface to restock."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:944
msgid "Wait! Look at that wall to the west!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:971
msgid "The water at its feet is moving. That can only mean..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:976
msgid "... that there is a stream on the other side. Well spotted! It should be worth a shot."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1006
msgid "These accursed bats are everywhere!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1011
msgid "It’s a cave, what did you expect? Rabbits?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1027
msgid "Those water creatures don’t look friendly at all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1038
msgid "What in Uria’s name?? These abominations look much like Yechnagoth’s true form did according to our druids. But how? Our ancestors purged them all!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1043
msgid "These tunnels had been completely inaccessible until now, so it stands to reason there could have been stragglers left trapped in here. But from what we learned back in Wesmere, these creatures should not be able to prosper if left to their own devices for so long..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1079
msgid "It seems there was a cave-in here long ago. The blocked passage might have led to the citadel back in day. Let’s see what lies down the other way."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1142
msgid "So this must be Argan’s old base of operations. We should see what we can find, but beware of its current residents — we may need to evict a few in order to progress."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1147
msgid "Gather all information you can from Argan’s lair"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1171
msgid "The bones of a human, it seems. Who knows how this poor bastard ended up thrown into this chamber."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1188
msgid "This gate doesn’t budge, and we don’t have more explosives left. There’s got to be a way to open it — we should look around."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. "Access granted."
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1225
msgid "Acc██s gr█nte██ ¢ 0█ B"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1237
msgid "Good thing this glyph <i>mostly</i> works still."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1266
msgid "It looks like this section is completely flooded; some parts have even collapsed seemingly from erosion. Whatever lies down there, I doubt it’s going to be of much use at this point."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1287
msgid ""
"S: Research Labs\n"
"SE: Manufacturing\n"
"SW: Catacombs"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1464
msgid "Crystal Glyph"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1496
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1518
msgid "This glyph may only be used by a true descendant of She who wields the Arcane Flame that protects Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1500
msgid "Elynia, you should check this crystal; it may have information we need."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1520
msgid ""
"Within this glyph lies encoded a <b>Teleport</b> spell which will allow you to cross great distances if you let your soul travel unimpeded by your body. Gaze beyond with your eyes closed, and touch the existence outside your reach. Given sufficient focus, you shall be able to transport your being to any place from your memories and find any soul within your heart’s sight.\n"
"\n"
"Yet cautiously you must tread, for not all the possibilities are written, and those who stray from their reality might not find anything on the other side of the mirror."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1526
msgid "That’s strange. Why would Argan keep something he obviously couldn’t use in his lair?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1531
msgid "Certainly this must be a trap intended to get rid of us or anyone else who would somehow manage to find this place."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1536
msgid "(<i>wistfully</i>) Or maybe... he foresaw me coming to this place and wanted to lend me a hand, even if he couldn’t break free from Uria’s control himself. He didn’t seem fully in control of his mental faculties in the end, but I don’t believe he ever intended to cause me any permanent harm."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1541
msgid "Elynia, what do you mean? He came horribly close to murdering you!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1546
msgid "He could’ve killed me with ease if he truly wanted, especially when I fought him up close while you were reduced to an inert pile of bones. Think about it: his biomechanical body granted him enough strength to pulverize stone and tear living creatures in half. Even as my staff violently clashed against his arms, he chose to continue attempting to subdue rather than eliminate me. Even when... Uria took control of his body... he resisted her enough to keep himself from squashing me like a bug."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1551
msgid "I’m taking the spell."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1556
msgid "Wait! Elynia, don’t—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1570
msgid "As Elynia grazed the crystal’s surface with her hand, the glyph instantly disintegrated into fine glistering golden dust, and furiously swirled all around her for a few seconds. The onlookers could only stare in horror as it suddenly covered her entire body..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1601
msgid "... and then swiftly vanished into thin air, revealing no visible harm on the faerie."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1610
msgid "I don’t feel any different, but... I guess I need to figure out exactly how this power works, now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1615
msgid "Elynia! Thank the Lords of Light you are all right..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1620
msgid "Hmph. In <b>my</b> times, you didn’t acquire magic abilities from shiny rocks. Be careful if you ever attempt to use that spell; knowing who most likely put it there, I really don’t think it’s safe. And more generally, while it is well known that powerful mages learned to travel across great distances like that, it also true that many of them randomly vanished leaving no trace behind."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1625
msgid "While I appreciate your newfound concern for my safety, Malin, I am very well aware of all this — so spare me the lecture."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1731
msgid "There doesn’t seem to be much more to see here due to the lower levels being completely flooded. It’s really unfortunate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#. "Our priestesses won’t accept this truth." or something similarly terrifying.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1737
msgid "What we have found here though, is... frightening, to say the least. We always thought that there was only Irdya, not this... nonsense. Our priestesses won’t... What— what do we do with this?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1742
msgid "The ‘First’ is also described in the ruins of a hidden city beneath the Heart Mountains. It is said that he created ten powerful demons, the Original Ten. All this would imply that all elves and other faerie creatures are descended, or at least created in the image of this mysterious wielder of the Arcane Flame, sister of Uria and Yechnagoth, and one of the Original Ten."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1747
msgid "Eloh. That’s her name — a name that was seldom heard in my times, for nearly nothing was known for certain about her and the myths neglected explaining the origin of every other race on Irdya. I suppose that Zhangor’s influence upon Wesmere may have resulted in the reintroduction of that name to our kin’s lore. Regardless, even though linguistics are not my specialty, I suspect that’s still not her true name, much like the case of Yechnagoth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1752
msgid "What you have learned here about all this... it would probably be best to keep it a secret for now, especially the allusions to other worlds. In these times when demons roam and spoil Irdya at will, realizing that they might be closely related to us, and that there might be even more awaiting out there... it could be devastating to our cultures. Perhaps after all this is over..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1757
msgid "<i>(snicker)</i> You said that Argan never intended to cause you any harm? All that we have found proves that he really wanted to destroy your kind after all! Using the powers of an ancient demon, no less!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1762
msgid "I don’t believe that he did any of his plotting against elvenkind out of his own volition. He was... under Uria’s control."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1767
msgid "So, have you forgotten what he said? “I guess I had this coming ever since then.” I know, his last words were very vague, but it certainly sounded like he was well aware of what he was doing the whole time. Perhaps you are right and it was not his intention to cause harm to <i>you</i> in particular, but the damage he caused throughout the continent, in the name of Uria, to the things you protect... did it not affect you emotionally? Furthermore, it seemed like Uria truly felt his loss. Would she have resented his death so much if he was a mere puppet like that old elf guy?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1789
msgid "Elynia slowly approached Mal Keshar with a grim expression in her eyes — neither the lich nor Galas had seen that much rage reflected in her before."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1804
msgid "You know nothing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1809
msgid ""
"I saw enough. I heard enough.\n"
"\n"
"Whoever you loved so deeply back then is not who died at your hand."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1820
msgid "<i>(nervously)</i> Er— I think we should return to the surface before we run out of provisions."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1825
msgid "Elynia... if I’m not mistaken, we found a journal in the Heart, and you have kept it all this time with you, correct?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1834
msgid "I... the elf who suggested that we take the journal, he was under Uria’s control, wasn’t he? It might not truly be Argan’s."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1839
msgid ""
"I am sure it is. I knew Lord Lédinor well enough, and I’m sure that was him speaking, not Uria. It was after we left Argan’s lair that his face and demeanor changed completely. No matter what Uria said, I’m certain that Lédinor was resisting her control just long enough so that he could help us, even though he must have known deep down that she would overpower him in the end.\n"
"\n"
"We are descendants of Eloh, and as the Quenoth elves can attest, not even Yechnagoth’s mind control can work on us that easily. Like Argan before him, it seemed more like his body was infected by some kind of parasite."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1850
msgid "I know you are probably hesitant about reading Argan’s journal because you fear to learn more about how he became the Emperor, and about the trail of destruction he left in his wake..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1859
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2817
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/01_Beyond_her_Smile.cfg:1549
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3924
msgid "I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1868
msgid "If you prefer, I could read it for you, and keep any details besides what is relevant to our quest from reaching anyone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1877
msgid "<i>(with a calmer expression)</i> Very well. I trust you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1882
msgid "In the meantime, perhaps you could socialize with the locals or something. Perhaps try to have fun and smile? It really helps when you’ve lived for so long — I should be one to know. While you do that, I’ll be <i>killing</i> myself reading a damn book; I haven’t found any good reading material since the Fall, you know? It seems like everyone suddenly forgot how to read and write after the Wesnothians singlehandedly ended the world!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1887
msgid "... You are already dead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1900
msgid "We have spent too much time in these caverns, and many of my men are starving. I’m sorry, but we’re resuming this expedition another time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07_The_Search_for_the_Past.cfg:1905
msgid "<i>(furiously sighs, staring at the ceiling)</i> Why do we <b>always</b> have a time limit of some sort for everything we do?"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:179
msgid "Resolutions"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:111
msgid "Vordel"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:115
msgid "Naron"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Galas, id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:119
msgid "Dela"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:131
msgid "It is certainly unfortunate that you couldn’t find a solution to this problem. Everything seems peaceful and good from our current location, but if Uria’s minions win the war and take over the continent, it will only be a matter of time until they come to claim this island. And what if Yechnagoth is able to control the surface creatures of the continent again?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:136
msgid "At least we know that her soul is no longer in this world. There’s a faint possibility that they might be unable to use her heart for anything yet. We must make haste and instruct our allies to purge the remains of Wesmere."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:141
msgid "A few of our people expressed interest on joining your group to help you in this quest, and learn more about the state of the lands whence we came a couple of centuries ago."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Dela
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:146
msgid "Eloh would want us to help our kin in these dark times."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vordel
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:151
msgid "Our numbers are very small, and we don’t have the resources to support an army, but we have the knowledge, and the faith to try to make a difference on the battlefield."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Naron
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:156
msgid "It would be an honor to fight alongside you, sir."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:161
msgid "Fight, indeed. We have spent too much time far from ‘home’ — who knows what’s become of it since we left."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:166
msgid "The honor is ours. We appreciate and accept your help on this day, but we are even more grateful for the day on which you released Irdya from the eternal nightmare of Yechnagoth’s control."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Maina
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:171
msgid "Young Galas, what you three have done for us is no small deed either. Although your journey is not quite complete yet, by defeating Uria’s designated sovereign of Chaos, you proved that her forces are not invincible, and rekindled that flame of hope everyone needed. You truly are the heroes of the forest elves of this era."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Gaellis
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:185
msgid "Kyara is one of our most skilled archers, and she has expressed her desire to join you in your quest. Seeing as how you will need all the help you can get, we thought you might welcome her support."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. "I’m not sure that’s a good idea."
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:191
msgid "I’m not—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:196
msgid "You can come with us if you wish, but you need to be aware of the dangers that lie in our way."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:201
msgid "I <i>am</i> aware. I’ve already talked with Lord Galas about it — I just want to be of help to our forest cousins in this struggle for our future."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/07x_Resolutions.cfg:210
msgid "Well, we must now prepare for departing tomorrow in the morning. A long voyage back home awaits us..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:94
msgid "Explore the peninsula"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:112
msgid "The fog is so thick I can barely see anything in the distance. It’s rather unsettling..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:117
msgid "Indeed. We should explore this peninsula carefully and stay together. Maybe we can find an abandoned castle or village where we can rest while we plan our next course of action."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:122
msgid "The air is unusually dense. There’s something more about this place I don’t like."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:127
msgid "We may soon find out..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Magus, id=Essornius
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:172
msgid "Essornius"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:282
msgid "What kind of infernal spawn is that thing?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:287
msgid "Shaxthals. We are definitely not alone here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:292
msgid "We’ll have to fight our way through this place then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:327
msgid "Yes, we did it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:332
msgid "Let’s leave this land as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:356
msgid "Galas?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/08_Fear.cfg:382
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1406
msgid "... Elynia?"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 1"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Chaos Razerman, id=Aethercyn
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:284
msgid "Aethercyn"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:378
msgid "Galas... you too..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:383
msgid "Well done, Kendria. Well done."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#. “master” here is feminine
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:389
msgid "I see that the little vermin fell into the master’s trap as expected. And they brought the Ruby of Fire with them! Ha, ha!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:394
msgid "What are you talking about..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:416
msgid "Keep it shut, pathetic Irdyan rats! Were it up to me, we would have killed you all on sight, but our master greatly wanted to see your faces one last time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:421
msgid "Temper your anger, my friend — after all, would it not be bad form to let their souls depart blissfully unaware of their mistake in bringing the artifact straight to us? Ha, ha!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:426
msgid "You... don’t have... a master... We killed... him..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:444
msgid "We have reserves, my dear."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:453
msgid "You...?! We should have finished you off... when we had the chance..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:458
msgid "Had you done that, someone else would have taken Argan’s position in my stead — someone less generous, perhaps, like our brutish colleague over here. Do you not wish to hear the story I have to tell you as proof of my gratitude? I am fairly certain Elynia in particular would love to know more about the significance of the little trinket she’s been carelessly parading around for so many generations."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Halbadrel
#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:463
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:487
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2228
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:797
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:835
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:851
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:861
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:987
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2104
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2279
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2284
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2289
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2294
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1761
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2143
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08C_Breakdown.cfg:2033
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3459
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4385
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:1044
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2949
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:523
msgid "..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:468
msgid "Irdya, like many other worlds, is littered with spatial anomalies that result in unstable pathways between them and Inferno. Long ago, it was decided that these breaches in our worlds should be guarded by very powerful demons to prevent unwanted contact. Think of it as a quarantine of sorts, established out of fear that the denizens of Inferno could interfere with the healing process that followed the First Cycle."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:473
msgid ""
"Alas, untold millennia ago, humans on this earth discovered that they could harness the forces of nature to overcome all sorts of challenges. Eventually they created a series of artifacts capable of building portals between locations on Irdya with ease. How, you may ask? My research never managed to uncover the specifics of the ritual, but all evidence points to them subduing some kind of dark god and using its blazing flesh and blood in the construction of these devices.\n"
"\n"
"But they were mere replicas of an original — without contact with it, the power within them eventually faded away. Meanwhile, the original was thought lost in a bloody war between the descendants of its creators and uncultured barbarians."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:480
msgid ""
"I thought this sounded familiar. For the longest time I had been in search of a relic of the old empire, one whose history started with a similar event. Could they be one and the same? After all, few people ever came close to grasping the true nature of the Ruby of Fire before somebody ordered its destruction. Yet... it was never truly destroyed, was it?\n"
"\n"
"My vast experience carrying out tasks for Uria gave me some familiarity with the power of the Gatekeepers, enough to identify it as its bearer unwittingly brought it before my eyes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:492
msgid "I could not believe my eyes — after wasting most of my original life trying to find it, the Ruby of Fire found <i>me</i> instead! Whoever would have thought that the staff that once belonged to the Enchantress Niryone of Wesmere had become a vessel of such ancient power! If only Argan had known about this — there would have been no need for us to trace the rifts created by Naia and her fallen sister in order to sustain our operations."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Nar-hamoth
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:501
msgid "Now that we have the artifact, we can use it to merge this pitiful world with Inferno..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:506
msgid "... dispel the curse of Iluvia..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:511
msgid "... and reunite Uria and the other Guardians..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:516
msgid "... to restore the Initial Order."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:578
msgid "Now this belongs to us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:585
msgid "At long last! The Ruby of Fire, in all its glory! May I borrow it for a second, my lady?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:614
msgid "This is not over yet!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:804
msgid "AAAAAAAAAAH!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:847
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/02_02_Reckoning.cfg:259
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:769
msgid "How did you—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:867
msgid "Kill the intruders! Kill them all! NOW!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:904
msgid "By the power you have bestowed upon me, Uria, may the spells conferring life to the dead be canceled now!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:907
msgid "dispel undead"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:944
msgid "AGGGGGGGGGHHHHH!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:949
msgid "What is this...?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:956
msgid "Unbind the dust from this world and smite the unworthy descendants of Xia’el!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:959
msgid "dispel faerie"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:996
msgid "This... is this the kind of powers possessed by Uria?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1001
msgid "We need to get out of this place, quickly!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1006
msgid "Kendria, call upon our new weapon."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Kendria
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1011
msgid "But we... we haven’t finished—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1032
msgid "Reinforcements! Don’t allow them to escape!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1114
msgid "That corridor is clear! It’s our only hope!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1123
msgid "Move Galas, Elynia or Mal Keshar to the exit location"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Hekuba
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1229
msgid "More reinforcements! Strike down those heathens, now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_1.cfg:1234
msgid "We weren’t fast enough — now they are coming from that corridor as well!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 2"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:172
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:208
msgid "Locate an exit"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:325
msgid "We must make haste before their reinforcements catch up with us. Which direction should we go?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:330
msgid "A slight breeze comes from the passage to our left; we should follow it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:335
msgid "These passages are eerily vacant. I feel we are being led into a trap of some sort..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:400
msgid "Mal Keshar, we’ll need some reinforcements to get through!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:426
msgid "Things are looking rather grim... We have not fully recovered from that demon’s attack, and her guards are in hot pursuit. Our backup has most certainly been scattered or slaughtered by now. What do you plan to do now that this has turned into a suicide mission?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:440
msgid "A gate! Let’s strike it down—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:494
msgid "It’s an ambush!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:499
msgid "Damn them all! I don’t know if I’ll be able to keep on with this for much longer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: type=Shaxthal Stormblade Ivyel
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:536
msgid "... Elynia... please... don’t..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:541
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/02_01_Return_to_Raelthyn.cfg:1092
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07B_Dark_Sea.cfg:2181
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3540
msgid "Huh?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:546
msgid "It’s running away!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:577
msgid "I— Hopefully it’s sufficiently damaged so that it won’t attack us from behind again. We need to advance, quickly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:899
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2137
msgid "What the—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:909
msgid "Amidst the smoke from the explosion, a pair of red glowing eyes could be seen..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:980
msgid "You thought you could escape so easily, didn’t you? I have not forgotten what you did back then. How does it feel to be the ones at a disadvantage now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:985
msgid "Elynia, Mal Keshar! Go! Now!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:992
msgid "Galas, no!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1037
msgid "Commendable effort, elf. Alas, not enough."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1110
msgid "It doesn’t have to be like this. Just give me the staff back and <b>I</b> will spare your life like you did with mine."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1129
msgid "Over there! Follow the track, quick!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1202
msgid "Follow the underground rail and locate an exit"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_2.cfg:1254
msgid "There are more of those biomechanical creatures pursuing us now. Oh, well, this entire plan was doomed to failure from the very beginning — I don’t know what I was thinking!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:4
msgid "The Triad — Part 3"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:229
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:163
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/00_Opening.cfg:537
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/07A_Dark_Fire_part_2.cfg:354
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2836
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2847
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3115
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2622
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/11_After_the_Storm.cfg:239
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:41
msgid "Elyssa"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:241
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1883
msgid "What now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:246
msgid "Let’s keep moving. Hopefully there is an exit somewhere ahead. Elynia—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:251
msgid "I’m fine — don’t worry about me! What about you?!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:254
msgid "You haven’t escaped, you know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:258
msgid "MOVE!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:265
msgid "It would have been so much better for all of you to give up..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:273
msgid "Galas... Why did you do that? Why did you charge straight at her? She could’ve easily killed you with a single blast of her fire!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:278
msgid "She is a formidable opponent for sure, but I desperately needed to buy you and Mal Keshar time to find a way out. It worked, didn’t it? Even though I did not count on you getting involved and doing... that. I’m not even sure how you managed to hit her so hard with only your staff."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:283
msgid "I heard you very well you back then — and you thought I would leave you for dead just like that?? I <b>refuse</b> to let you play hero now, after everything we have been through! Please, <b>please</b> don’t scare me like that again!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:292
msgid "... I am sorry, Elynia. I just desperately wanted to help you escape this place alive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:297
msgid "Galas, I... I just don’t want you to put your life on the line like that ever again. After everything we’ve been through, I need— we need to stick together. We can’t lose you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:306
msgid "I understand. I’m sorry."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:311
msgid "... I’m sorry too. I didn’t mean to sound so harsh, Galas. Just promise me you’ll stay by my side from here on."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:316
msgid "I will, Elynia. I promise."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:366
msgid "Uria be damned! It’s a dead end."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:371
msgid "It’s more like a trap—"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:374
msgid "You cannot blame me. I gave you one opportunity to reconsider your actions — I’m not giving you another."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:397
msgid "You made a big mistake in leaving the safety of the Northlands..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:416
msgid "—I knew it. We are trapped."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:421
msgid "Not quite — there seems to be a passage behind that crack on the wall!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:444
msgid "Elynia, the teleportation spell you learned back in Zocthanol! Can you use it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:449
msgid "I— I don’t know, it wasn’t really made to transport more than one person, and I haven’t had a chance to try it myself."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:454
msgid "This is probably not the best moment to fiddle with unpredictable kinds of magic like this. As I said before, many mages have disappeared attempting to master the power of teleportation."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:459
msgid "It’s an option to consider, nonetheless..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:579
msgid "This place stinks of <i>blood</i>. What’s with that water?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:584
msgid "I fear that it <i>is</i> blood, in fact. Something is really wrong. No single creature could contain so much of it. Who knows what kinds of twisted experiments these fiends perform in here?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:589
msgid "There truly appears to be no way out of this chamber. What do we do?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:594
msgid "I’ll tell you what: we shall create our own exit from this accursed place by tearing it all down from the inside!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#. The otherwise intended end of the sentence is: "try that teleportation spell now!".
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:600
msgid "Or we could take the risk and—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:666
msgid "G—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Lady of Light
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:707
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/08_And_then_there_was_Chaos.cfg:770
msgid "NO!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:722
msgid "You opted for doing this the hard way after all, didn’t you? The staff — hand it over now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:727
msgid "—I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:732
msgid "Elynia... we must..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:743
msgid "—I... I damn you, Elyssa... I damn you and your kind... for this..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:756
msgid "My dear, we were damned long ago by the First Gods. Your petty words are irrelevant in the grand scheme of things. Hand it over now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:761
msgid "Elynia, the spell!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:770
msgid "Don’t you see? We aren’t that different after all. You just lost your new beloved just like you lost Argan. I lost <i>much</i> more than that long ago. You think he was important because you never had to endure the cruelty and ruthlessness of the beasts that dare call themselves ‘humans’."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:775
msgid "Stop listening to her, Elynia!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:796
msgid "What a waste. Don’t think you’ll find anything of value in Wesmere."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/09_The_Triad_part_3.cfg:839
msgid "That’s it. We are now utterly lost in these infested passages... and the worst part is that I was the one who devised this disastrous rescue plan."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/10_Tears.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/storytxt.cfg:311
msgid "Tears"
msgstr ""

