#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:997
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1310
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1550
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:1618
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:2321
msgid "You will not be able to recall or recruit any units until the end of the mission"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:933
msgid "Locate Yechnagoth’s heart"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:947
msgid "Somehow, this place seems much larger than it was last time we set foot in it. Then again, we did intentionally avoid venturing deeper into the hive as we were in a rush."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:952
msgid "So, from what you said we are looking for a roughly-spherical scarlet gem-like artifact, about the size of a closed fist and which gives off a very distinctive aura, which may or may not be embedded in some sort of shell. Are we absolutely sure it’s not been relocated since Argan wrote about it? Neither last time nor now can I feel anything of importance other than Zhangor’s taint."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:957
msgid "As I understand, these things are much like oil lamps and their intensity can be adjusted at will, or even turned off entirely when not in use. Argan’s lead is all we have for now, I fear."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Mal Abaddon, type=Chaos Lorekeeper
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1048
msgid "Mal Abaddon"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#. The "fated one" he refers to is Elynia. As world lore will reveal in the
#. next scenario, Mal Abaddon took part in a program codenamed "Thornfire".
#. As part of the program, both he and Mal Si'ah had access to privileged
#. information about Elynia's true nature, that they were under oath to not
#. divulge to anyone else, not even the Iron Council.
#. Meanwhile, neither Elynia nor Mal Keshar are heeding his words; even though
#. Mal Keshar knows quite a lot more than he lets on at this point, he's not
#. interested in listening to Chaos preachers.
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1076
msgid "O fated one, led astray by the non-believers! I pray that the Mistress of the Void takes pity on your soul. Come forth and hear the truth!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1081
msgid "I would roll my eyes if I had any."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1118
msgid "A prayer for your salvation!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1126
msgid "Only ruination awaits those who willfully transgress into the territory of the divine."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Abaddon
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1139
msgid "O fated one... your pilgrimage continues. May peace... find... you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1151
msgid "What’s the point of turning themselves into these hideous biomechanical abominations if they are just as mortal as before? Oh hey, I seem to have found something in his robes. Let’s see..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1160
msgid "I also found what appears to be a miniature version of those crystal glyphs."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1165
msgid "These things must be very important if one of their high-ranking priests was carrying them around. I shall keep them safe."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1207
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1305
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/09_New_Hive.cfg:310
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/11_A_Final_Confrontation.cfg:880
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1363
msgid "Access granted."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1243
msgid "We should have access to the lower levels now. Onward!"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Dante, type=Chaos Arbalestier
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1267
msgid "Dante"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1337
msgid "So glad we did not need to fiddle with the glyph to get this gate open."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Return_to_Wesmere.cfg:1343
msgid "The area up ahead seems very different to the rest. We must be on guard."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: race=orc,goblin,faerie,human,elf, type=Shaxthal Drone
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:4
msgid "Wesmere Terminus"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:195
msgid "Terminal Hub C1"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:200
msgid "Genetic Repository C3"
msgstr ""

#. [label]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:205
msgid "Power Plant NW-ß"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:529
msgid "Search for clues as to the whereabouts of Yechnagoth’s heart"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:547
msgid "The group proceeded into an enormous chamber, carved deep into the bowels of the earth through clearly artificial means. Some of the technological structures around seemed to have been long in disuse, with evident signs of weathering, while others appeared to have been recently operated or even rearranged."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:552
msgid "Still no sign of anything out of the ordinary, as far as I can perceive. (<i>sighs</i>) We’ll need to sweep this place if we hope to locate that accursed artifact. How well could these self-important wretches possibly conceal the remains of a god they worship so fervently, anyway?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:604
msgid "Locking us in already? Do they seriously expect us to be deterred by a rusty metal gate?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:609
msgid "Something doesn’t seem right. Someone is clearly watching our every move and doesn’t want us to leave — yet, it remains eerily vacant in here. Not to mention that surely they would do anything in their power to keep us from reaching Yechnagoth’s heart."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:614
msgid "Well, it’s not like you could ever resist the allure of a trap like this, anyway. We came in here ready for anything, so let us get working on that investigation now! It might not be in here but we may be able to at least find more clues."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:676
msgid "Level 5 clearance required. Access denied."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:681
msgid "Hmmm, Elynia, this crystal glyph seems to want some sort of identity proof. Remember that crystal we got from the custodian of this place? You should try bringing it here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:700
msgid ""
"Operator credentials verified: Mal Zagarn\n"
"\n"
"Access granted."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:707
msgid "Mal Zagarn... it can’t be..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:712
msgid "I remember I saw the name somewhere in the documents we pilfered from their capital... The name of the founder of Uria’s cult... Argan. He was here after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode1/scenarios/12_Wesmere_Terminus.cfg:717
msgid "Bear in mind someone else could have borrowed — or even ‘borrowed’ — the crystal from him. It matters little to us, anyway. Shall we see what information we can squeeze out of this shiny rock?"
msgstr ""

