#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:125
msgid "I remember hearing of the mandate issued to destroy the Sceptre of Fire back in the day..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:134
msgid "I’m curious about why you decided to betray your people by keeping the Sceptre’s core to yourself, Elynia."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:139
msgid "That’s nothing of your concern."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Keshar
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:144
msgid "It is not, really? Because to me, it seems that you carry with you a dangerous artifact that these people <i>need</i> for some vaguely-defined purpose that will most certainly bring no good to this world! Destroying it would be the most logical choice right now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:149
msgid "... I beg to differ, but with the Union gone it may well be the only great power remaining on Irdya that we could use to fight Uria and the Iron Triad, unless you know something I am not aware of — which I find unlikely."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode2/scenarios/00_Transience.cfg:154
msgid "This isn’t the best moment to argue over this."
msgstr ""

