msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:659
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:676
msgid "Secure the portal located within the central keep"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:710
msgid "Aran-Balgur is really impressive. How could it fall to Uria’s forces?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:715
msgid "Some people say the lord of the stronghold was brutally killed by the Chaos thugs on the battlefield some time after their Emperor fell. The man left in charge in his place wasn’t very bright, and couldn’t stand a chance when the angry enemy troops arrived. Others say they found the descendant of the architect who helped build its walls a century ago, and forced him to reveal the plans with all the secret passages and weak points."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:720
msgid "Regardless of the rumors, the fact is that they killed everyone. See the stains on the exterior walls? Everyone says it’s the blood of the former occupants. Some believe that the General’s family was amongst them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:725
msgid "I guess... that explains why he’s such an unpleasant person."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:744
msgid "I hope everyone is ready for the battle ahead of us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:749
msgid "We are, my lady. What are your orders?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:754
msgid "Just assist our allies with the siege and deal with whatever creatures guard the keep and the rumored portal. We ought to make this quick, for the demoness that awaits us at the other end might not be too patient, and this mission has delayed us too much already."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:759
msgid "You haven’t changed your mind..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:764
msgid "Indeed, I have not."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:790
msgid "I don’t like that sound..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:809
msgid "It is time. At last... I’ll have my revenge..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:814
msgid "And what about us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:819
msgid "You two shall be allowed to leave once the battle is over — that is, assuming you survive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:824
msgid "What if we lose?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:829
msgid "Should it come to that, you’d best hope those fiends will be swift to end your pitiful lives."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:834
msgid "That’s truly motivating..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:843
msgid "Durvan, what are you going to do after this is over? You said earlier you had some doubts about Elynia’s plan, and you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:848
msgid "Yes, I won’t be going with you. Her plan just seems too risky... What the hell is she thinking? Didn’t you say Elorran himself knew his kinsmen couldn’t be trusted? Besides, I won’t be very useful once you arrive there. From what I’ve heard, the natives hate us, and motivating and talking to people is really all I have done ever since I joined Elynia."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:853
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:2912
msgid "But..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#. The other human is Erathan from IftU.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:859
msgid "You two and the necromancer woman have all those magic abilities and powers I will never have. I’m tired of risking my life fighting alongside you against powerful demons and psychotic cultists. I just... I just want to live a longer life than the other human Elynia got killed in enemy territory, the poor bastard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:864
msgid "Heh, yes... But you were really brave in the valley..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:869
msgid "I was really <i>stupid</i>! I hadn’t heard of that guy and his fate yet!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:879
msgid "I still think I will miss you... even if you only rarely start a conversation! And I’m sure Elynia will miss you as well."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:885
msgid "Sure..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:894
msgid "I wish you two all the luck in the world. You’ll surely need it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:909
msgid "I want this to be over as soon as possible so I can bid farewell to the giant wolves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:914
msgid "Why? They are so cute!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:919
msgid "Nope, they’re terrifying. And they smell."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:929
msgid "What about Willow? She’s so fluffy and cuddly and..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:934
msgid "I <i>really</i> don’t like her. She follows me around as though she knows I am terrified of her."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:939
msgid "Awwww, but she just wants to be your friend! You should give her a chance!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:944
msgid "<i>(sighs)</i> I don’t think this is the right time and place to practice shock therapy, Anya. Maybe when things have calmed down a little."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1193
msgid ""
"In this scenario, most units under your control can carry barrels of explosives, which can be used to destroy structures and other units.\n"
"\n"
"To retrieve a barrel, move a unit over it. You will be given the choice to grab the barrel or leave it for another unit. Once a unit gets the barrel, it will gain the <b>Demolition</b> ability, allowing it to destroy everything within a one-hex radius upon death. The unit will also be able to <b>drop</b> the barrel for another unit to pick it up, or <b>deploy</b> an activated charge. Once a barrel is deployed, it will <b>destroy</b> everything within a one-hex radius at the start of the next first-player turn, so you want to make sure your unit has enough movement points left to get away before deploying.\n"
"\n"
"Units lose the Demolition ability after dropping or deploying barrels.\n"
"\n"
"Use these barrels wisely! You start with a limited number, and you need at least <b>six</b> to complete the main objective!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1226
msgid "Deploying these explosives so close to your encampment would be an incredibly ill-advised idea!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1249
msgid "That is not an appropriate location for deploying these explosives. Try elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_deploy
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1331
msgid "Deploy Charge"
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_siege_charge_drop
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1356
msgid "Drop Charge"
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Elynia.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1471
msgid ""
"elynia^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"The thought of leaving this world with yet another explosion is inviting at this point, but you have been through that in three different occasions already, and survived to get this far. What would the point be? Perhaps Anya is right, and there is still much more left to do before your time comes. You want to find that demoness in the Pass of Sorrows first, after all."
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Anya.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1479
msgid ""
"anya^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"That sure was a silly thought to entertain! But your hope has not waned just yet, and Elynia needs your help. You are determined to stay at her side until it is all over. She is all you have left, and perhaps more than you will ever have."
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Kyara.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1487
msgid ""
"kyara^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"That pointless exercise of thought promptly leaves way for recalling the stories of your people’s arrival to Quenoth Isle. Many say they were assisted in their journey by dwarves, underground dwellers with an inclination to devise this kind of evil artifact. You decide it may be for the best that a civilization with such destructive potential confined itself to the caverns beneath the surface."
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Durvan.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1495
msgid ""
"durvan^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"But you would not be caught dead carrying such dangerous materials. As everyone knows, your craft is hunting prey; you ain’t anybody’s transport man."
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is Igor.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1503
msgid ""
"igor^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of “boom” artifacts all by yourself. You wonder whether Elynia and her new friends would regard your action as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"Upon further thought, however, you realize that giving up on the peaceful street perform life to become fireworks goblin is probably not quite what people mean when they talk about “going out with a bang”. Not to mention you could not possibly bring yourself to leaving poor Willow alone in this nasty, cruel world. Perhaps you will look into procuring a safer source of “boom” at a later time, you think to yourself — something like one of those fire sticks that high-ranked Chaos officers carry around these days. Your mighty steed gives you an approving nod."
msgstr ""

#. [case]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up the barrel
#. is the General Bardyl.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1511
msgid "bardyl^You contemplate one of the barrels of explosives your superiors sent from Fort Rylgur before the Far North fell to those infernal bastards. You feel glad that you are not one of the poor nameless soldiers who were charged with the task of carrying these to Aran-Balgur’s main keep!"
msgstr ""

#. [then]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up a barrel
#. is one of the other female heroines.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1519
msgid ""
"female^You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your actions as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, you are not so stupid as to attempt such a pointless move now."
msgstr ""

#. [else]
#. This message is used when the unit attempting to pick up a barrel
#. is one of the other male heroes.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1526
msgid ""
"You silently consider the possibility of rushing into the battlefield carrying this heavy barrel of explosives all by yourself. You wonder whether your comrades would regard your actions as heroic or foolish.\n"
"\n"
"In any case, you are not so stupid as to attempt such a pointless move now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1574
msgid "The unit you have chosen for this task is not able to lift the weight! Try another unit."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1589
msgid "Should this unit carry the barrel of explosives?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1591
msgid "Yes, pick up the barrel."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1601
msgid "To drop or deploy the charge, right-click on the unit and choose the desired option from the context menu."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1608
msgid "No, let someone else do it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1641
msgid "You cannot carry more than one barrel at once!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:1848
msgid "Blast it, we have wasted our explosives on the battlefield instead of saving them for the main keep! We can’t continue like this — retreat!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=General Bardyl
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2030
msgid "Destroy that enormous monster before it gets a chance to rain its fire upon our troops!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2058
msgid "Custodian of Aran-Balgur"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2058
msgid "Protector of the Chaos Stronghold"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2282
msgid "But... how?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2287
msgid "Shapeshifters. They are somewhat different to other demons in that the more mature individuals are much harder to kill without arcane magic than the rest. (<i>disgusted</i>) It’s said they are basically extinct, but some demon lords still keep them as slaves."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2292
msgid "How do you know that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2297
msgid "Well, Elorran did tell me a lot of things about them..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2306
msgid "(<i>muttering to herself, aside</i>) ... mainly because I am one of them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2319
msgid "Battle goblin strikes again, yes! Take that, wretched scum!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2324
msgid "He’s got an endearing quality to him most of the time, but I’m still not quite sure whether I <i>should</i> be concerned about his more bloodthirsty side...?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2329
msgid "Nah, I think he’s all right. You too have your moments despite being cute most of the time, after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2334
msgid "<i>(blushing)</i> Well... thanks, I guess."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2356
msgid "Finally, that thing was a real nuisance."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2369
msgid "Are you leaving now, Elynia?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2374
msgid "Well..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2376
msgid "Yes, I think it is the right time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2380
msgid "All right, then."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2387
msgid "No. Our allies still need our help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2391
msgid "As much as I dislike General Bardyl and his people, we wouldn’t have achieved this victory without them. I think it’s best to assist them until the battle is over. But I’ll keep the portal in mind if things don’t go as planned later."
msgstr ""

#. [set_menu_item]: id=wmi_leave_battle
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2396
msgid "Leave Battle"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2436
msgid "If you change your mind later, you can choose the <b>Leave Battle</b> option in the context menu by right-clicking on any unit or vacant hex."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2447
msgid "Do you really wish to leave the battle?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2450
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3580
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3635
msgid "Yes."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2456
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3197
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3608
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:3719
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:361
msgid "No."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2519
msgid "Call more reinforcements! We can’t afford to lose control of this region to these wretches!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_01_Outpost_of_Hell.cfg:2540
msgid "Let us find that portal."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:186
msgid "Gateway"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:168
msgid "I guess I have to admit I am hesitant to continue..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:177
msgid "He said it was a greater cause, after all. I fear that once we step into this portal... We might never come back to these lands alive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:182
msgid "Why do you want to come, anyway? Haven’t all my decisions led to awful disasters since we began? All our victories have been small in the grand scheme of things, and many have died because of my desire for answers... and revenge."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:209
msgid "Elynia... While all that is true, you can’t deny you have helped us all do more good than any of us alone could otherwise. No-one is perfect..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:214
msgid "... not even gods, as it turns out."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:223
msgid "... But most importantly, we work as a team! I for one promise I won’t give up in the face of danger."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:228
msgid "Neither will I, my lady!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:233
msgid "Yes, I know. Galas never gave up either..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:238
msgid "Nor did Mal Keshar."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:243
msgid "... That is true... too true."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:252
msgid "I understand that you won’t be joining us in this suicidal mission, Durvan, so... What will you do?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:257
msgid "Eh, I will just stay safe and sound here and help defend the castle until I find a way to return home. Maybe try to convince that general or Lord Torancyn—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:262
msgid "<i>Supreme</i> Lord Torancyn. (<i>snickers</i>)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:267
msgid "... They might be willing to send someone to check the situation in Kalari if you can secure the portal from the other side."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:275
msgid "I hope that is the case, yes. Bardyl seemed rather grateful for our assistance at the end of the day."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:281
msgid "I doubt Bardyl will understand that I simply could not tarry here for longer than strictly necessary, especially since ‘my’ little band failed to live up to his expectations. And Torancyn... I wouldn’t bet on his support at this point."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:288
msgid "Many of our men seem willing to follow you. I just don’t know what their motivation is — money, bloodshed, adventure? It’s rather strange, really. But I’m sure you could use their help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:293
msgid "What will you do, Horo, Kyara?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Horo
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:298
msgid "Well, returning home is out of the question for me with Tirigaz gone. Those vermin will surely head back here as soon as they hear of our victory, presumably led by that hideous demon midget... Right now, there’d be nothing more satisfying for me than breaking his stumpy neck and wearing his hollow skull as a helmet."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Kyara
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:303
msgid "As soon as I may, I’m returning to Quenoth Isle to spread the word about all these events... Perhaps, if the war comes to an end first, we could even send some people back here, to trade with the humans and orcs... I know that’s all very unlikely with the current state of things, but... (<i>shrugs</i>) dreaming never hurt anybody."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/04_02_Gateway.cfg:312
msgid "I guess so..."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:321
msgid "Pass of Sorrows"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:110
msgid "Vissalen"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Ancient Lich, id=Algessel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:147
msgid "Algessel"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:221
msgid "team_name^Unknown"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:279
msgid "Explore around"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:295
msgid "There’s absolutely <i>nothing</i> hinting at this place having served as a Chaos base of any sort in recent times. It’s completely deserted and ruined. I fear we have been misled. We might not even be in Kalari for all I know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:300
msgid "No. I recognize that mountain range to the south. We... we never saw what lay north of it. We are a little farther from Kalari than I expected, but it’s not like any of us—or our allies—knew exactly where the Pass of Sorrows is. Let us proceed south, carefully."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:314
msgid "Igor, do you think you could help watch our backline for any potential attacks from the north?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:319
msgid "Awww, but I wanted to help..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:324
msgid "I have seen that you prefer a more frontal approach to battle these days, but right now my main concern is that we don’t get ambushed. You will still be able to help by alerting us of any possible threats."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:329
msgid "If you think that’s the best way I can help then I’ll do it, my lady. Let’s go, Willow!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:347
msgid "The solitude of this place is unsettling."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:368
msgid "Ugh. The fog is getting thicker..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:430
msgid "Elynia, Irylean... you should see this."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:453
msgid "These ruins appear to be centuries old — probably older than the Chaos Empire itself. I imagine they have remained untouched by our enemies because of their inconvenient location. What may have become of their former denizens?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:458
msgid "There’s a large monolith over there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:493
msgid "Elynia should be the one to investigate this monolith."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:518
msgid "I don’t understand this inscription — some glyphs vaguely resemble the ancient ceremonial Elvish script, but I don’t recognize the rest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:525
msgid "The wind blows."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:530
msgid "Wait..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:601
msgid "... Mal-Zagarn..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 3
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:607
msgid "... come..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=ruins ghost 2
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:613
msgid "... she..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:622
msgid "Wh— What’s going on?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:627
msgid "This pass is inhabited by restless spirits of the past! My lady!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:706
msgid "There seem to be more undead creatures crawling out of the caverns to the south. Perhaps if we can clear them out we’ll find a way out of this valley."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Algessel
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:718
msgid "Thank... you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:740
msgid "The lich’s staff is glowing! What could it possibly mean?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:762
msgid "Free..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Vissalen
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:771
msgid "... at last..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. [message]: speaker=Ethealim
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:776
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1486
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08A_Interim.cfg:1492
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:64
msgid "Who are you?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:808
msgid ""
"Many centuries ago, our ancestors came from the Great Southern Desert seeking fertile lands to settle. They gave up much to get to this valley: their lives, their families... Most of them died along the way. The few survivors found a ruined temple amidst the mountains, probably built by an extinct civilization. From that temple they learned the ways of fire magic, and the song of Shardia, She who forged knowledge from the fire of our hearts.\n"
"\n"
"They thrived with their newfound skills and the protection granted by the precipitous mountain range. They continued to learn from Her, and longed for the day when She would come to this earth and bless it with Her song. And in time, so did we.\n"
"\n"
"Until..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:816
msgid ""
"One day, a man shrouded in darkness came. His eyes were bright like Naia’s never-ending shine; his mouth, concealed by twisted metal and decayed flesh. His companions called him Mal-Zagarn.\n"
"\n"
"He spoke a message from the so-called Goddess of Life from beyond the Void, Uria, who had tasked him with the mission of spreading her voice to all non-believers in this land. But other than the Goddess who gave us our fire magic, we would worship no-one, especially not someone who only communicated through an embodiment of the unnatural like that dark prophet. And so we dismissed his words as the blasphemous ramblings of a barbarian.\n"
"\n"
"In time, we would be proven wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:822
msgid ""
"Years later, the man returned, but not with a handful of trusted followers. Instead, he brought with him innumerable horrors from the Abyss to rain acid and smoke upon our homes. He gave our leader a last chance to convert to his unholy sect.\n"
"\n"
"That is to say, <b>I</b> was offered that last chance.\n"
"\n"
"Everyone was slaughtered. Everyone except me, my brother, and a child with beautiful hair, whom we believed was the heiress of Her fire; for never before we saw one of our own be born with the same hair color as our Goddess. But just like the scrolls and books we hoarded, we eventually lost her to the walking vultures of the desert, who took her as their own. They spared her life, seeing as she was but a child, but our own fate was vastly different."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:828
msgid ""
"The Goddess of Life had cursed us to linger in this form, and dwell in the caves beneath the earth in shame. The light of the suns we once revered became a scorching enemy by day. Our fire magic was quickly displaced by shadow magic as we could no longer even withstand the heat of our flames. We had too become embodiments of corruption, a mockery of the beings we once were.\n"
"\n"
"We vowed to take revenge upon the dark courier who brought disgrace upon our kind, and anyone who was ever close to him or his followers. Either we would be destroyed and released from our prison, or our curse would be extended to the creatures we abhorred.\n"
"\n"
"But it is all over now."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:834
msgid "We may still be able to find Her on the other side of the Veil, and bask in the glory of Her song..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:864
msgid "Argan..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:873
msgid "Elynia..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:878
msgid "I— I am fine. Don’t worry about it."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:947
msgid "Proceed to the southern cavern exit with Elynia"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:973
msgid "We don’t know what lies outside. Are you sure you want to proceed, my lady?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:978
msgid "Allow me to ponder this for a moment..."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:980
msgid "Yes, I think it’s time to go."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:986
msgid "No, let us see whether there might be something else of value in these caves first."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:990
msgid "Very well."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1091
msgid "A lone troll?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1098
msgid "He bears an unusual sigil on his armor for a troll..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1109
msgid "Hail there, whoever you are. Are you our enemy?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1119
msgid "The old battle-hardened troll stared at the sky for a minute before answering, while Anya and Irylean eyed each other nervously."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1124
msgid "Cron works for no-one but the storm lady."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1129
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) Elynia, would that be..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1134
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) Yes, I think so."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1139
msgid "Cron, if you allow me to ask, where is this person? We... may or may not have arranged a meeting with her, here. This is a quite urgent matter, and... Are you even listening to me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1144
msgid "(<i>pointing at the sky</i>) There."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1178
msgid ""
"The demoness descended from the sky in an impressive whirl of dust and leaves. Anya and Irylean stared in awe, and immediately knew they would be at a disadvantage if she were, in fact, their enemy. But Elynia did not have an opportunity to entertain such thoughts. She could tell at first glance that in spite of her young age, the Demon Lord of the Storms was not the type that would take admiration and other displays of weakness very well.\n"
"\n"
"After all, she had risked it all and come only to enlist powerful allies for her dwindling cause."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1185
msgid "(<i>whispering</i>) All right... I <i>think</i> these two look rather frightening..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1190
msgid "Ergea, Demon Lord of the Storms, I suppose?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1195
msgid "That is correct, Elynia, the Lady of Light. I have been eagerly awaiting this moment for weeks. What took you and your party so long? I heard you hired the services of the northerners to prepare an assault to the gateway fortress, instead of infiltrating it on your own. That wasteful spectacle could have ruined our plans."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1200
msgid "And your plans are intended to help us, or is this just part of a convoluted scheme to catch me off-guard near your headquarters?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1205
msgid "My priority is putting a halt to Uria’s schemes, preferably while keeping collateral damage to a minimum. There just are not a lot of people these days who can truly be trusted. I had to ask the human seer to deliver my message to you because sensing people’s intentions is not one of your powers, and you have committed too many mistakes as of late in that vein, much like Elorran."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1210
msgid "Elorran...?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1215
msgid "I tried to warn him that Zhangor sent his new pets after him, but that fool never allowed my minions to approach him or his informants. I assume he never told you that—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1226
msgid "Repeat that name."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1233
msgid "Zhangor?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1238
msgid "How...?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1243
msgid "He recently became the Fist of Uria. I thought Elorran and you of all people on Irdya would be aware of this."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1252
msgid "Elynia? You don’t look good..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1259
msgid "Wh— why...? Why is he here? Why is he... on Irdya... again? I— I did everything within my power to... to..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1264
msgid "Destroying a shapeshifter of his level is nigh impossible; and frankly, you never truly learned to employ the Power of the Union effectively. Argan and you played around with it like children instead of working towards harnessing its full potential. But I don’t blame you. There is a lot you need to learn right now, and I can help you with that. However, we are running out of time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1269
msgid "Will you help me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1274
msgid "I came to seek your help only because our goals converge on the ultimate purpose of ending this war. I can only help you if you are willing to help us — and first I need to speak to you in private."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/05_Pass_of_Sorrows.cfg:1283
msgid "... Very well."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:331
msgid "Divergence"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:49
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:107
msgid "Talk to Anya before going to sleep"
msgstr ""

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#. [effect]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:137
#: After_the_Storm/macros/items.cfg:395
msgid "staff of akhlys"
msgstr ""

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:138
msgid "Immune to poison"
msgstr ""

#. [trait]: id=staff_of_akhlys_lvl1_tag
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:139
msgid "The wielder of this staff is immune to poison."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:297
msgid "Still awake? You haven’t slept well in months."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:302
msgid "I just can’t get to sleep knowing that we are in this land, Anya — it brings back bad memories."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:307
msgid "I understand."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:318
msgid "Discuss your plans with Anya."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:321
msgid "Speak to Anya about Ergea."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:324
msgid "Ask Anya a question."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:334
msgid "I am still worried about tomorrow. Ergea said reinforcements were coming for us, but we have not gotten confirmation from Aran-Balgur and that damned portal closed on its own. And regardless, it would be foolish to rely on Bardyl and his people."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:339
msgid "We still have the undead, and surely Ergea wouldn’t lie to us?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:344
msgid "I suppose not, but her sources might not necessarily be the most reliable. For all we know, they could have already betrayed her. They might be leading us to a slaughter, and—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:349
msgid "(<i>holding Elynia’s hand</i>) I am sure... that with Ergea’s power and yours, we can do this. The bulk of their forces went north, the Triad is now missing that disgusting lich... and we will be joined by those reinforcements soon — I hope. And if we are meant to die here, then we’ll all die fighting for a just cause."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:354
msgid "... Well, yes..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:359
msgid "But somehow, I feel that everything will go well!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. "Us" here being Anya and Irylean.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:367
msgid "Elynia, what was it like talking to Ergea? She seemed quite, uh, intimidating to us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:372
msgid "I got the impression that she’s simply been through too much in her life, and it’s surely not her fault. From what I gather, Urvatha, the world we usually call Inferno... is decidedly not the best place to live. Demon Lords competing for succession and killing each other all the time, oppressing and enslaving their subjects, and Uria coercing them into doing her bidding by abusing the ancient powers she was granted by destiny... "
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:377
msgid "I can only say that Ergea is a much nicer person in reality if you know how to approach her."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:382
msgid "Hm. (<i>smiling</i>) I guess you would have enjoyed talking with Elorran, too."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:387
msgid "I guess."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:394
msgid "So, why did you not tell us that you were a shapeshifter?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:403
msgid "(<i>surprised</i>) I... What are you talking about?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:408
msgid "I did hear your quiet remark when we were fighting those creatures in Aran-Balgur. Having spent a considerable part of my life in the wild, did you expect any less? I imagine your sense of hearing is just as good despite your smaller ears."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:413
msgid "Well... I... I think I have never felt comfortable with my heritage. After all... it is the very reason of my abandonment as a child..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:418
msgid "I can only wonder why I wasn’t raised by my real parents. Who were they? Could they still be out there, alive? But on second thought... perhaps I don’t want to know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:423
msgid "If I had told you from the very beginning that I am a shapeshifter, you would have never trusted me. How can you trust a creature who could be concealing their true appearance and nature?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:428
msgid "Are you, though?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. 'We' being demonkind.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:434
msgid "No! But that doesn’t change the fact that you would have distrusted me back then! I mean... more than you did. You were always so distant and obsessed with your duty... almost like an emotionless machine, just like you have always assumed <i>we</i> were..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:439
msgid "<i>(sighs)</i> I guess I still am. You could call it a coping mechanism, I suppose. I originally became a druid to help others, not to take people’s lives. All this bloodshed... it could have been avoided if I hadn’t made all the terrible choices that led me here — the same choices that led to the downfall of this world. Nobody in this era would remember, but I am in large part responsible for bringing the people who ultimately doomed us all to the throne of Wesnoth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:444
msgid "When you are forced to live through the consequences of your mistakes, when it’s not in your nature to kill but you have no choice... you begin to put reality aside just to keep yourself in one piece. Instead of being the one doing the killing, you are watching someone else do it for you. Sometimes it may even seem like an enticing distraction from your own thoughts."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:449
msgid "Other people recall good memories to comfort themselves in times like these, but each day that passes I struggle more and more to remember anything other than my worst moments: the utter destruction of an era of balance and life, the fall of my people, the horrors wrought by Zhangor... the blood of my husband, in my own hands and drawn with my own power... and my... friends... killed or destroyed in front of me... before I could do... do anything to prevent it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:458
msgid "... I fear it, Anya... I fear what would happen if I allowed myself to be controlled by my emotions."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:467
msgid "Elynia... I’m sorry, I did not mean to make you feel like this."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:476
msgid "... No, I am the one who should apologize. Perhaps if I shared my feelings with other people more often, I— I wouldn’t be like this..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:481
msgid "I haven’t lived for a thousand years, but I know that it is true — you would feel at least a little better if you talked to someone about whatever troubles you instead of blindly killing creature after creature to distract yourself from the pain."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:486
msgid "Perhaps... you could do that? Talk with me more often?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:495
msgid "Yes, I could... If we survive this encounter, that is."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:500
msgid "But you must promise!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:509
msgid "... I... I promise."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:514
msgid "(<i>smiling</i>)"
msgstr ""

#. [then]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:529
msgid "Go back to sleep <small>(move Elynia back to the encampment keep)</small>"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:546
msgid "Ask Cron about Ergea."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:549
msgid "Ask Cron about tomorrow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:559
msgid "If I may ask, for how long have you been serving under Ergea’s banner and why?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:564
msgid "Cron works for the storm lady since his home in the mountains was taken by the flying metal-shells. He was promised things in return for protection."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:569
msgid "Protection?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:574
msgid "The storm lady does not trust the masked men and their rusty swords. She prefers help from Cron and the lizard people of the swamps. She feels safer this way."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:579
msgid "What kind of things did she promise to you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:584
msgid "The lady promised us a new home if we can help her kill the Iron Council and their leader, Zhangor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:589
msgid "Hm, is her intention to seize Kalari for her own people and allies then?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:594
msgid "Cron must not discuss the storm lady’s plans with anyone else."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:599
msgid "... Fair enough."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:606
msgid "There’s a lot of things awaiting us tomorrow, and we will need all the help we can get. Do you think your people will accede?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:611
msgid "Cron is very sure they will, but they are not many, and they cannot help as much as they want."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:616
msgid "A little help is better than nothing — Ergea said we would be getting reinforcements, but I don’t find that likely to happen."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:621
msgid "The storm lady always says the truth."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:626
msgid "Yes... that’s very true... Too true, perhaps."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:647
msgid "Talk to Irylean."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:650
msgid "Ask Irylean about her retirement."
msgstr ""

#. [value]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:662
msgid "Ask Irylean about the Staff of Akhlys."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:682
msgid "You seem very weary, my lady. Shouldn’t you be getting some sleep?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:687
msgid "Yes... But you know the situation with that. So, do you think your disciples will be able to help? Can they be trusted?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:692
msgid "They have proven to be quite reliable thus far, haven’t they? Unfortunately, I can’t know whether they intend to betray us at the end like your previous assistant did, my lady. If they were consorting with our enemy they’d make sure we wouldn’t find out until it was too late."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:697
msgid "Indeed. That’s why I am worried. If only Galas were still with us... He always seemed to make the right choices."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:705
msgid "Hm... perhaps."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:711
msgid "Hm... perhaps. Then again, was it not his choice to give that ring to a cute little bat? Heehee."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:716
msgid "I– Malin told you about that? Oh gods, why... What even possessed Galas to do that?? That ring might be gone for good now. Although... I have to admit that would be a preferable fate than having it wind up in the hands of another omnicidal demon one thousand years from now. Just... please don’t tell anyone else what happened."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:721
msgid "Worry not, my lady. My lips are sealed!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:730
msgid "If you don’t mind the question, why did you retire before?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:737
msgid "I guess it was a combination of circumstances... I felt Galas’ decision to delegate the government of your people to those four was horribly ill-advised. Then you all decided to go south and... I knew that wouldn’t end well for me. From what I heard that fellow Erathan didn’t fare well in the capital."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:742
msgid "That’s unfortunately true. And I suppose I owe you an apology for forcing you to come here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:747
msgid "Bah, nobody can force me to go anywhere if I don’t want to!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:752
msgid "So, what were your motives?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:757
msgid "My lady, I am old, and I already spent enough time in the Far North to know that it could never be my home. Plus, it is because of these bastards that my master’s time in this world came to such an abrupt end. You know what I mean with this — I have seen it in your eyes, your thirst for revenge and how you quench it with the blood of your enemies..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:762
msgid "I do not want to talk of that now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:767
msgid "Well... my apologies if I have offended you, my lady. It was not my intention. I’ll just... go back to watching over the encampment, silently, as usual."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:783
msgid "So, did you solve your little problem with that staff?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:788
msgid "Well, yes. It’s quite interesting, actually. It turns out that with some adjustments to my shielding spell, I can channel the staff’s aura and become immune to poison myself!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:793
msgid "... And that would be why you asked me to heal you from the symptoms of a ‘cold’ at least ten times during the day, right?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:798
msgid "... Right."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:803
msgid "I mean, if you think it’s safe to use the artifact like that, I’m in no place to stop you. My knowledge of necromancy is not exhaustive enough to know exactly how that staff works or whether it might be hazardous to its user. Just... be careful when using it near our people, please?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:808
msgid "I will be, my lady, don’t worry!"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:833
msgid "Talk to Igor."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:836
msgid "Ask Igor about his time in the northern country."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:839
msgid "Ask Igor about Anya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:849
msgid "Everything all right, Igor?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:854
msgid "Yes... I guess. It’s just that I can’t stop thinking... The elf friend died in these lands."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:859
msgid "... Yes. Yes, he did. I am sorry, I couldn’t do anything—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:864
msgid "No, there was nothing you could do. The demon lady knew what she was doing. She’s a trained assassin or something, isn’t she? I have seen how my kind do it. Quickly, cleanly. Their prey falls to the ground already dead. You can’t heal the dead. Nobody can."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:869
msgid "I just regret not coming with you... Maybe then things would’ve turned out different, you know. If we had all been together?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:874
msgid "Perhaps. I don’t think it would have changed much, though. If anything, you would have been in danger as well and I don’t think I could have managed to pull all three of us out of that accursed citadel in one piece. Mal Keshar barely made it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:879
msgid "I know... I’m sorry. I need to stop beating myself up about it — I’m just a goblin after all, fighting things I really don’t understand in the middle of something much bigger than me. Not battle goblin, just... goblin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:884
msgid "Don’t say such things. Your time will come when you will be able to show everyone that you can accomplish great things despite the labels they force upon you, Igor. I am sure of it. I believe in you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:889
msgid "That’s actually the nicest thing anyone’s ever told me... Thank you, my lady. I just wish the elf friend and the scary lich were still with us. I miss them a lot."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:894
msgid "So do I, Igor. So do I."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:901
msgid "How did your adventures in the Aragwaith country go, anyway?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:906
msgid "Oh, uh, about that..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:915
msgid "Kinda disappointing really."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:920
msgid "Go on."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:925
msgid "Well, you see, I didn’t do any street performing for most of it. I first found this gloomy old man in a tavern in a frontier town. He told me a buncha vague stuff and left? After that I did errands for random people for something like an eternity. I even helped save a town from a fire! And then I remembered... he told me to search for a lady seer and bring her to the capital... but I nearly got myself killed while searching for her all over the north. I’m not even sure why I did any of that — I kept hearing the old man’s words in my head like a command."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:930
msgid "Old man? Who was he?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:935
msgid "Dunno! He never told me who he really was, but... you know that feeling like you’re doing something really important and you can’t mess it up? That’s how I felt about the whole thing, even though thinking back I realize... if it hadn’t been me, it could’ve been anyone else, right?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:940
msgid "... Yes, I think I know what you mean. Somehow that sounds familiar... But my head hurts if I try to remember, it must have been too long ago, before the Great Fall."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:945
msgid "I’m sorry lady Elynia, I just needed to get that outta my chest. I know it doesn’t make sense but sometimes I’m afraid that maybe I did mess up in the end."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:950
msgid "It sounds like our paths almost crossed at the capital back then, though. I wonder why I never found you there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#. Yes, apparently Igor doesn't realize that what he calls 'water longbirds'
#. are actually swans.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:957
msgid "Welllll, you see, sometime after taking the seer lady there, the city guard kicked me out on orders from the heavy swords guy because of something to do with the “local swan population”? Dunno what that was all about, Willow only eats water longbirds anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:962
msgid "... Really, now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:967
msgid "Mhm!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:974
msgid "You seem to be getting along well with Anya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:979
msgid "Yes! And the purple lady likes Willow a lot. I’m so used to everyone being afraid of her for no reason even though she’s just a big puppy. The archer guy, for example — he’d constantly avoid her. I don’t understand why."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:984
msgid "I don’t think he and the other people from the Heart Forest are fond of wolves in general. They have their reasons."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:989
msgid "If you say so... But let me ask you, how come you don’t mind the demons all of a sudden?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:994
msgid "It’s complicated. It is not so much that I don’t mind them, but rather that I have seen that reality isn’t as black and white as we thought. Ergea and her people... they have their own conflict with Uria going on. It turns out there is no shortage of Demon Lords who tried to wage war against her in the past to escape oppression. But all those attemtps were doomed to fail, until now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:999
msgid "It is now up to me... to <b>us</b>, to make a difference. Tomorrow we shall fight for the fate of Irdya, and if we succeed, then Inferno will follow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1004
msgid "That sounds great and all but I don’t like the way she looks at me scrunching up her nose every time she passes me by..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1009
msgid "Oh, uh... that... that might just be that she has difficulty breathing the air of Irdya. I think."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1014
msgid "Oh, I see. Nothing to worry about then!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1069
msgid "Anya..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1105
msgid "Good night."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1110
msgid "Sleep well!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1207
msgid ""
"elynia^You purposefully enter your tent for the last time before the inevitable confrontation with your enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Fully aware of the odds, you decide to grab a few things you know you will need — except for your journal, that is. You also opt to leave Argan’s and Galas’ journals behind, along with a note."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1215
msgid ""
"elynia^When done, you give your enticing makeshift bed a final glance. Anya is right — you have not gotten any proper sleep in what seems to you like ages, and this could be your last opportunity to rest in your entire life.\n"
"\n"
"But you have different plans for tonight."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1234
msgid "Talk to Cron"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1256
msgid "elynia^You silently approach Anya. Just as you expected, she is still wide awake and completely attentive to her surroundings. But she obviously was not counting on your stealth spell. You shudder to think what would happen if Uria’s underlings decided to use similar magic to dispose of you and your friends in the middle of the night."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1262
msgid "elynia^You feel terrible for having to resort to such a tactic yourself. Hopefully she will understand in time."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1276
msgid "Tell Cron you are leaving now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1286
msgid "It’s time, Cron. Please take care of Anya in my absence."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Cron
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1291
msgid "Cron will do his best to make sure nothing bad happens to the storm lady’s friends."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1319
msgid "Leave the encampment"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1380
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08B_Destiny_part_1.cfg:1024
msgid "Hm."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1391
msgid "Elynia, are you there?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/06_Divergence.cfg:1438
msgid ""
"N: Pass of Sorrows\n"
"S: Kalari Peninsula\n"
"SE: Kalari Central"
msgstr ""

