msgid "Nortrang"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Faerie Dryad, id=Meeryn, type=Faerie Dryad, id=Anelith, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Sharazkas, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Eressin, type=Demon Spelldancer, id=Domegi, type=Saurian Flanker, id=Issylias, type=Orcish Warlord, id=Nortrang, type=Direwolf Rider, id=Fernol, type=Orcish Slayer, id=Acengrez, type=Orcish Slurbow, id=Bogar
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:670
msgid "Fernol"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Faerie Dryad, id=Meeryn, type=Faerie Dryad, id=Anelith, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Sharazkas, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Eressin, type=Demon Spelldancer, id=Domegi, type=Saurian Flanker, id=Issylias, type=Orcish Warlord, id=Nortrang, type=Direwolf Rider, id=Fernol, type=Orcish Slayer, id=Acengrez, type=Orcish Slurbow, id=Bogar
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:681
msgid "Acengrez"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: type=Faerie Dryad, id=Meeryn, type=Faerie Dryad, id=Anelith, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Sharazkas, type=Saurian Soothsayer, id=Eressin, type=Demon Spelldancer, id=Domegi, type=Saurian Flanker, id=Issylias, type=Orcish Warlord, id=Nortrang, type=Direwolf Rider, id=Fernol, type=Orcish Slayer, id=Acengrez, type=Orcish Slurbow, id=Bogar
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:711
msgid "Bogar"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:739
msgid "For the last time, Durvan, I am <b>not</b> a goddess! This is ridiculous!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:744
msgid "Well... there’s not much you can do about it at this point, anyway. Everyone saw the darkness stuff you did with the remaining monsters, and rumors spread like—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:749
msgid "A disease! I do not even know what I actually did! I only want to leave this dreadful place and rest!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:754
msgid "This is the most auspicious moment to storm the citadel if that is what you want to do. And if you play the part you may be able to obtain support from Uria’s converts. Once they realize that the Fist and the Iron Council have been lying to them, the Chaos Empire’s social structure shall shatter. But we ought to plant the seed of distrust now, while Elynia and the Fire prepare to vanquish the usurper."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:759
msgid "... Assuming they are even alive."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:764
msgid "Is that what you want?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:769
msgid "... Yes."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:772
msgid "I want to see her once again. I want to talk to her, smile with her. She promised..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:776
msgid "Then, please, help us. Help us storm the citadel. Help us uproot Uria’s evil influence on Irdya, and advance the long path that lies ahead for you as the Guardian of Darkness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:794
msgid "I guess I should be thankful you are not calling me Merthiaal or anything like that."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:799
msgid "The names of the guardians you know were the names they chose for themselves in the First Cycle. We may not call you by the name of the original Guardian of Darkness unless you choose to adopt her name instead of your own."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:804
msgid "Is that how it really works? I prefer to keep my current name, then."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:813
msgid "Hey, Durvan, did you ever think you would fight at the side of two faerie goddesses against an endless horde of demons, imps, and devout worshipers of an evil demoness?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:818
msgid "No. Well, now that you mention it... this will be quite the story to tell the folks in the Heart Forest. Nobody will ever believe me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:823
msgid "Same..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:837
msgid "On the bright side, dying and returning to the physical realm as a Guardian is a surprisingly easy way to get rid of all the sweat and filth on me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:851
msgid "Igor?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:856
msgid "Hm?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:861
msgid "Have you ever felt like... no matter how hard you try, you can’t even hope to measure up to someone whose company you enjoy?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:866
msgid "Uh, sometimes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:880
msgid "But you end up realizing that friends don’t expect you to magically become something you’re not! Lady Elynia and the scary lich always were way more than me with all those magic powers I don’t understand, but that never stopped them from seeing me as a friend!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:885
msgid "Right. <i>(sighs)</i> I guess I’ve just got to accept it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:909
msgid "Oh, hello again!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:914
msgid "Greetings."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:919
msgid "I thought something bad may have happened to you back there... You were with us and then disappeared? Why?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:924
msgid "You need not worry about my wellbeing, Anya. I can easily escape from certain danger thanks to my intimate connection to the Aspect of Water. There is a large amount of it around these parts, after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:929
msgid "Please don’t tell me now that you are the Guardian of Water or some nonsense like that... I cannot take more of this right now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:934
msgid "It would be a sin beyond measure for someone such as I to pretend to be a god in front of one. With that said, all faeriekind creatures are connected to one or two Aspects to some degree. For example, you are connected to both Darkness and Earth as the daughter of a forest faerie."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:944
msgid "Right, which reminds me I still don’t know how the story of my parents ends. Then again... perhaps I don’t want to know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:951
msgid "Did you know I was meant to become the Guardian of Darkness, though?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:956
msgid "Yes, I did. And I apologize for not revealing that to you — if I had, there is a good chance that you would have made all the wrong decisions."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:964
msgid "Meanwhile, Ergea hasn’t apologized for keeping information from me... Which reminds me, we still have a battle to fight. I hope I can count on your help."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:970
msgid "Meanwhile, Ergea hasn’t apologized for keeping information from me... Well, it doesn’t matter for now. We need to get back to the fight."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:977
msgid "Certainly."
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1115
msgid "The prophecies were correct! The Dark Lady was reborn, and she has finally come to vanquish the usurper and set us free from his grasp!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1117
msgid "Rise up, brethren! We are slaves of the Fist no more!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1119
msgid "May the Dark Lady guide us to victory over the false god!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1121
msgid "Can it be? Rebelling against Uria could be highly disastrous for everyone! But... What else do we have left anymore?"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1128
msgid "We have long awaited this night. Together, we shall forge a new empire from the blood of the usurper and the fakes who dare to adore him!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1130
msgid "Uria’s time is almost over. I can feel it. Death to the usurper!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1132
msgid "Behold, the Guardian of Darkness in all her godly glory!"
msgstr ""

#. [set_variables]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1134
msgid "Let us cleanse this land and restore the true cult of Yechnagoth!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Mal Ba'arth
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1340
msgid "... It is true, then. The Dark Lady has finally arisen and come to reclaim this doomed world... But it is all in vain... all in vain..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1494
msgid "The citadel is ours! Now we should be able to find Elynia and—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1505
msgid "I fear that we will have to put that plan on hold, Anya. There are reports of more of those creatures coming from the hives around the citadel. People say they will be here in a matter of minutes."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1510
msgid "But we have only just won! Are they going to storm their own capital now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Durvan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1515
msgid "I would not put it past them to attempt to destroy the citadel in an attempt to ensure we cannot find Elynia... assuming she is even alive at this point."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1520
msgid "Do <b>not</b> say that! Let’s repel those awful creatures, then!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Irylean
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1525
msgid "Easier said than done..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Igor
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1530
msgid "Battle goblin, ready to crush those bugs!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1544
msgid "The Storm Sisters are now our prisoners, but we must destroy the last member of the Iron Council if we intend to seize the citadel."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Ergea
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1552
msgid "The last member of the Iron Council is no more, but as long as any of the Storm Sisters still roam about, there shall be no end to our struggles."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/08D_Destiny_part_2.cfg:1711
msgid "The earth rumbles..."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=Elynia
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:418
msgid "Dark Depths"
msgstr ""

#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:106
msgid "team_name^Engineer"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:515
msgid "... We are not really trying to locate Zhangor, are we?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:520
msgid "Of course we are. It is just taking us a while because he prefers to dwell in a very particular place... a place I also want you to see, before confronting him. I also want to give him a while to realize his mistake in interpreting the Seer’s prophecy."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:525
msgid "What mistake?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:530
msgid "The Seer said that on the Day of the Longest Night, the Angel of Blood would make a hasty attempt on the life of the New Guardian of Darkness, and fail. She also said that his actions would bring forth his own downfall."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:535
msgid "Zhangor must have decided to send his beasts after Ergea and your friend first, and then wait in his lair for me to go and challenge him — or alternatively, for Naia to rise up again. It would be a clever plan to subvert the prophecy, if it weren’t for his completely incorrect reading of it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:540
msgid "He doesn’t realize that the Guardian in question is that girl, who he already confronted and failed to kill. And you might not realize this, but it has been <i>more than a day</i> already — simply put, the Longest Night will not end until the girl puts an end to her emotional turmoil and learns to control her powers."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:545
msgid "Anya’s powers... So she is the cause for the Longest Night?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:550
msgid "Indeed, she is. I would explain more, but I suspect Zhangor is already aware of our movements. Let’s not keep him waiting longer than strictly necessary, shall we?"
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:576
msgid "You pick up a curious crystal shard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:659
msgid "Where does that lead to?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:664
msgid "It’s an alternative path to an elevator shaft that will take us directly to the place I previously mentioned. While I don’t mind stabbing whoever stands in our way, a more discreet approach will get us there faster."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:681
msgid "Only a fully corporeal unit such as Elyssa or Elynia may activate this touchplate."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:766
msgid "Nothing happens."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:777
msgid "These passages have gone unused for centuries — it’s no wonder that most of their mechanisms have rusted beyond use. But I know a method that never fails..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:783
msgid "These passages have gone unused for centuries — it’s no wonder that most of their mechanisms have rusted beyond use. Just blast the wall down already."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:833
msgid "Perfect."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:861
msgid "That is not very useful—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:870
msgid "Hm, there is a hot current of air coming from another direction now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:896
msgid "Ah. I remember now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1007
msgid "We need to cross this inconvenient lava trench. Elynia, do your thing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1012
msgid "My... thing?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1017
msgid "You are the Guardian of <i>Earth</i>, dear. You are supposed to be capable of more complicated things than blasting walls and vermin."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1022
msgid "Do you really expect me to know how this works all of a sudden?! I did not ask to be given this role, and all I know is that the pain has not ceased! I cannot think clearly like this!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1031
msgid "I <i>really</i> should just stab you in the chest and toss your useless bloody corpse into the lava."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1060
msgid "Keep moving."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1105
msgid "Well, this wall is not going to move by itself—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1111
msgid "Well, that wall is not going to move by itself—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1145
msgid "I stand corrected. That was very convenient."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1204
msgid "Of course. A cunning trap by Zhangor, I presume?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1238
msgid "The elevator..."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Engineer Fendyrn, type=Dwarvish Engineer
#. [hidden_unit]: id=Engineer Fendyrn, type=Magnum Suit
#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1277
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1397
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1501
msgid "Engineer Fendyrn"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1293
msgid "<i>... heh, heh, heh, heh, heh, heh...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1302
msgid "Who is that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1311
msgid "Engineer?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1321
msgid "<i>... hah, hah, hah, hah...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1326
msgid "You lack the required clearance to be around these levels, Engineer. Return to your workshop immediately."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1331
msgid "I dinna’ listen tae orders from ye anymore, witch. Yer time as the ‘Warlord’ ended with Lord Zhangor’s arrival."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1336
msgid "I believe I speak for Zhangor as well when I say that you are not supposed to be here. Return to your workshop immediately, or face the consequences."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1341
msgid "Ye’ll chop me remainin’ leg too, winna ye? Ha, ha, ha, ha. Yer torture methods are as obsolete as the tech’ Argan used tae rebuild yer body."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#. "Squirming insects" refers to the Shaxthal.
#. "The two of you" refers to Elyssa and Zhangor, not Elyssa and Elynia.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1348
msgid "Zhangor released me a while ago, didna’ ye hear? “Yer free”, he said. “Ye can do anythin’ ye please”, said. And so here I am, ready tae take on the two of ye, and all yer squirmin’ insects."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1353
msgid "Is this insubordination I hear? This is your last chance."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1358
msgid "I believe ’tis yer last chance tae <i>run</i>, girl."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1471
msgid "Oh gods... Is that..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#. The lich is Mal Hekuba.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1477
msgid "Aye. The Soul Hammer is made’a the crystals commissioned by tha’ wretched lich. Lord Zhangor has put many a’them intae good use, elf. But he dinna’ ken ’tis hammer exists, or that it shall be the instrument of me revenge! Perhaps I should’a named her... the Destroyer o’ Gods!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1482
msgid "Elynia, this is extremely dangerous. Stay away from this lunatic and his hammer! You, fool... you have absolutely no idea with what kind of powers you are trifling."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1487
msgid "<b>HA, HA, HA, HA, HA, HA, HA, HA!!!</b>"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1501
msgid "Tortured Inventor of Infernal Contraptions"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1509
msgid "Stop the Engineer"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=engineer_backstabbing_hint_handler # wmllint: ignore
#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1556
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1516
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1857
msgid "The power of the Engineer’s hammer allows him to debilitate and destroy the Energy Heart of a Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1517
msgid "Elyssa and Elynia cannot damage the Engineer’s armor suit as it is powered by more replicas of Merthiaal’s heart; they must find another way to stop him"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1528
msgid "I have an idea... Malin once mentioned something specific about Galas’ first encounter with your mechanical automatons."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1533
msgid "And what would that be?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1538
msgid "They are particularly vulnerable in the neck region. Maybe if we could distract him, you could stab him with your weapon—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1543
msgid "That was already my plan, stupid! Just try to do your part right for once!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=engineer_backstabbing_hint_handler # wmllint: ignore
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1548
msgid "Backstab the Engineer using the Claw of Urvatha while he is facing Elynia"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=engineer_backstabbing_hint_handler # wmllint: ignore
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1555
msgid "You can only backstab the Engineer during your own turns, on offense"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Engineer Fendyrn
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1840
msgid "<b>ACK!</b> What ha’ ye done!!!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1845
msgid "Oops! It seems your armor suit and fancy hammer are not perfect substitutes for the power of a true Guardian of Darkness!"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1850
msgid "Defeat the Engineer now that he is vulnerable to attacks"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:1938
msgid "Elynia, grab my hand!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2143
msgid "Unngh..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2161
msgid "I did not know where I was. The last thing I could recall was the chamber floor collapsing due to the energy released from the dwarf’s fractured hammer."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2163
msgid ""
"My neck felt cold and sticky... it was blood. I must have smashed my head during the fall, and yet I was standing there as though my body had healed itself from the otherwise fatal injury.\n"
"\n"
"I glanced at my surroundings..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2179
msgid "Elyssa...?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#. Yes, Elynia is describing a literal BSOD (Blue Screen of Death).
#. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_Screen_of_Death
#. Looks like Norsulan technology isn't perfect either!
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2191
msgid ""
"The demoness was lying on the humid cavern floor, inert as a rock. She did not seem injured, but neither did she draw breath. I did not know at first what to make of the situation.\n"
"\n"
"I laid a hand on her forehead and attempted to peer into her mind to see whether she was still alive. However, all I could see through her frozen eyes was a series of incomprehensible white glyphs on a blue background, interspersed with an alien and yet somehow familiar language. Knowing she was a hybrid lifeform, the evidence I gathered was useless."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2195
msgid ""
"She could be alive... or she could be dead.\n"
"\n"
"And not too far from her was the weapon she called the Claw of Urvatha. My master’s staff, first corrupted by the heart of a Gatekeeper, the artifact we used to call the Ruby of Fire, and now, by the malignant touch of Merthiaal’s successor."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2203
msgid ""
"I felt compelled to grab the weapon and leave the demoness behind... but I had to ponder my possibilities first. She could come back to life the moment I laid my hands on it, and destroy me. Or she could stay as a dormant machine, and I would just abandon her and return to the surface, with Anya and Ergea.\n"
"\n"
"A third alternative then occurred to me. I could grab the Claw, and destroy the creature in her sleep..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2211
msgid ""
"... I spent some amount of time contemplating that tempting alternative.\n"
"\n"
"Suddenly, the thought of becoming a cold-blooded murderer horrified me.\n"
"\n"
"No.\n"
"\n"
"No, I would not give in to such terrifying ideas. No. That was not me. That was not the elf who was raised by Niryone to protect the peoples of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"No."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2233
msgid "Between tears, I could catch a glimpse of light coming from around a corner."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2250
msgid ""
"A conspicuous corridor, leading somewhere brightly illuminated. The walls were decorated with peculiar engravings.\n"
"\n"
"I was compelled to follow. With my captor completely incapacitated to exert any kind of magic control over me, I could once again move with absolute freedom."
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2293
msgid "Explore the place"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2323
msgid "It was not my intention to go back where Elyssa’s inert body laid. I needed to keep exploring the corridor. My curiosity was just too great to resist."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2393
msgid ""
"The ceiling lights formed a familiar shape on the floor: the sigil of the First Guardian of Earth, Xia’el. Or at least, as it was depicted in Argan’s journal.\n"
"\n"
"An odd sense of comfort suddenly came to me. I felt for once as though I was, finally, at home."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2411
msgid ""
"If Elyssa spoke the truth, this was my destiny all along. I was meant to be the Guardian of Earth on Irdya, and I was meant to keep my world and my people from harm; from Elyssa, from Argan, from Zhangor, from Uria...\n"
"\n"
"... From myself.\n"
"\n"
"... And I had failed. I had failed them all. I grew up ignorant of my true purpose, focusing only on mundane problems, selfishly centered on my own needs and desires for the most part. I allowed Irdya’s terrible fate to come to pass: the destruction of many civilizations, the deaths of millions.\n"
"\n"
"Weren’t Guardians created to <i>protect</i> their worlds?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2438
msgid ""
"I let myself collapse on the floor... and cried.\n"
"\n"
"I needed to cry after Galas’ death. I needed to cry after losing Malin. But I resisted the emotion for so long because I did not want anyone to know I was weak inside.\n"
"\n"
"But then, I was at home at last... alone. Nobody would know. So I cried.\n"
"\n"
"I wished Anya could be with me. But she did not know where I was, and I did not even know whether she was still alive. And even if she was... it would only be a matter of time until Zhangor solved the Seer’s riddle and killed the girl."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2450
msgid "Home..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2456
msgid "There, there."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2462
msgid "You have not failed yet, my love. There are still things left to do."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2468
msgid "... A— Argan?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2474
msgid "... Oh, I must have really lost it now."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2480
msgid "I am here. Don’t you feel me?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2486
msgid "... Is this a dream?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2492
msgid "... Is it?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2498
msgid "... I feel you. I feel your warm touch again. But... how?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2500
msgid "Because you wished for my return. All these years..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2502
msgid "... I did."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2504
msgid "I missed you, Elynia."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2506
msgid ""
"... I— I—\n"
"\n"
"... I did too.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2516
msgid "We don’t have much time left, my love. Irdya is in ruins now, and Zhangor could find us any moment now. You need to get up."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2518
msgid "Yes..."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2556
msgid ""
"I let my lips approach his as we embraced like we had not for an eternity. He felt so delightfully real, I was willing to give in to our carnal urges.\n"
"\n"
"But..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2566
msgid "Is there something wrong, my love?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2571
msgid "I... feel... strange."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2580
msgid "My heart... it hurts..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2585
msgid "That must be because you have spent too much time scurrying around. Just let yourself relax for a moment. We can reminisce about better times together..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. Yes, the question mark may seem misplaced, but it's actually intentional
#. as it denotes a different sentence inflection. She is supposed to sound
#. confused.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2599
msgid "You don’t sound like yourself? My head... I—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2604
msgid "My memories have become so hazy... but... I... remember that sword... Elyssa has your sword..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2609
msgid "Elynia, please, just..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2624
msgid "Hello..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2677
msgid "... Zhangor."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2688
msgid "How..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#. I guess I'm already pushing the censors' limits a lot here?
#. It'd be advisable to keep it subtle in translations too.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2695
msgid "Your act seems pretty cheap in retrospect. I cannot say I am completely disappointed, though; it was <i>absolutely</i> amusing to watch you attempt to—ahem—handle the poor, broken elf. But did you truly think it would work out? Ha ha ha!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2700
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) I am not precisely here in person, though.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: id=Deathbringer, type=Shaxthal Deathbringer Alpha
#. [unit]: id=Deathbringer, type=Shaxthal Deathbringer
#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Deathbringer, race=shaxthal, description=
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2745
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1208
#: After_the_Storm/units/shaxthal/Shaxthal_Deathbringer.cfg:6
msgid "Deathbringer"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Deathbringer
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2777
msgid "But your guess was close enough. Congratulations, Guardian of Darkness."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2782
msgid "So the rumors are true, after all — you go around possessing other creatures using your disgusting body ooze."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2787
msgid "(<i>enraged</i>) You were going to possess me..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Deathbringer
#. "Aspect" here refers to the Aspect of Earth, not Elynia's physical appearance.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2793
msgid "Now, now, possessing a Guardian as vulnerable and inexperienced as you could hardly be considered a feat. <i>Consuming</i> you and stealing your aspect, though... would that not be something? Alas, it would seem you both wish to perish instead."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2816
msgid "(<i>enraged</i>) Not if I can kill <b>you</b> first."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2843
msgid "Defeat Zhangor’s Deathbringer"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2850
msgid "The Deathbringer’s spear allows it to destroy the Energy Heart of a Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. [unit_type]: id=Shaxthal Deathbringer Alpha, race=shaxthal, description=
#. That's a greek alpha. Translate as it seems more
#. convenient for your target language/font.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2863
#: After_the_Storm/units/shaxthal/Shaxthal_Deathbringer_Alpha.cfg:8
msgid "Deathbringer α"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. That's a greek alpha. Translate as it seems more
#. convenient for your target language/font.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:2866
msgid "The Demon Lord’s Puppet"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. As part of the eerie ambience for this section, the JourneyLog UI gets
#. "corrupted" as well, along with other parts of the game interface.
#. This text is a direct quote of IftU S10y - The Fall, in which Elynia
#. introduces the Ka'lian.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3121
msgid ""
"<i>The members of the Ka’lian valued knowledge over all other things\n"
"\n"
"They sought to plunder all the secrets of Irdya for the greater good\n"
"\n"
"In time, this would bring about our downfall</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3470
msgid "Hello?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [case]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3479
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4771
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2601
msgid "Niryone"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Niryone
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3483
msgid "Back from Filinor’s class early?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3502
msgid "He twisted his ankle yesterday morning while hunting with Cerin, so he let us go after a short round of questions."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Niryone
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3507
msgid "Bah. Figures. At least that means we can enjoy a nice midday meal together for a change."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3518
msgid "Sure, that would be great! I’m starving."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Niryone
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3531
msgid "Don’t come with me. It’s too dangerous."
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. Urvenirdrya is an archaic name for Urvatha (Inferno)
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3575
msgid ""
"Head severed\n"
"\n"
"Eyes blinded\n"
"\n"
"Limbs scattered\n"
"\n"
"Deep beneath Urvenirdrya\n"
"\n"
"I have waited"
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3589
msgid ""
"As a low-level unit under your control, Elynia has no special <b>After Maximum Level Advancements (AMLAs)</b>. You can learn more about those by 4 Ł vª§Ð t¬ þ ä\n"
"ŋ ½5 °5 é’   ⅞ Ý  T*  4    $$º ©      ŕ     `¬     _ē → fv     ’     ±        ¡"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is a direct quote of Elyssa lifted from UtBS S2
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3606
msgid ""
"<i>I accidentally managed to anger a powerful necromancer a while ago...\n"
"\n"
"It’s a long story\n"
"\n"
"But who are you?\n"
"\n"
"You almost look like elves</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3647
msgid "Niry? Where did you go?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. IftU S23B callback.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3655
msgid "<i>You are... hurting me...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3659
msgid "Final Objective:"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is Elynia's side of an exchange in which Argan
#. is proposing to her. She accepts.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3675
msgid ""
"<i>Argan, are you sure about this?\n"
"\n"
"Tragedy appears to follow me wherever I go\n"
"\n"
"And we may not be able to see each other for long periods of time\n"
"\n"
"I know, but...\n"
"\n"
"Immortality does little to assuage the passage of time\n"
"\n"
"I could never love anyone else as much as I do love you, my Argan\n"
"\n"
"My love...\n"
"\n"
"Yes...\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan, my love...\n"
"\n"
"Yes, yes, I would</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [case]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3704
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2615
msgid "Anlindë"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3706
msgid "<i>Don’t you realize that he will murder them all if you continue this pointless crusade of yours? Just leave them be, please!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3713
msgid "<i>Don’t you dare speak in that tone to me, foul priestess! You should be grateful we do not cut your tongue off for your insolence. Guards! Escort her out, now!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is Elyssa's voice, in a flashback to her imprisonment prior to
#. dying and being 'rebuilt'.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3766
msgid ""
"<i>Please, let me go\n"
"\n"
"If you let me go I swear will never trouble you again\n"
"\n"
"Please...\n"
"\n"
"Please...\n"
"\n"
"I beg you...\n"
"\n"
"I just want to go...\n"
"\n"
"Please...\n"
"\n"
"I can’t...\n"
"\n"
"I can’t...\n"
"\n"
"I just want to go...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3790
msgid "The Lady of Light and the Master of Darkness must die!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3795
msgid "Stop! Why are you doing this?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. "Them" = the elvish peoples
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3811
msgid "<i>I do not suppose I can convince you to abandon them now, after so long. Am I right?</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3818
msgid "<i>Of course not.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3828
msgid "<i>Then... we shall do this. Together.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3839
msgid "<i>... Together.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is Elynia's voice, again only her side of an exchange
#. with Argan.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3853
msgid ""
"<i>Ever considered returning to your land?\n"
"\n"
"I’m sure there must be a way\n"
"\n"
"From the things you’ve told me, it sounds so beautiful\n"
"\n"
"“Earth”? That’s not very original, is it?\n"
"\n"
"I mean, Irdya is often called that as well\n"
"\n"
"“Naalirdrya”? That’s such a mouthful, my love\n"
"\n"
"“Norsula”? Norsula... Hm, I like that\n"
"\n"
"Well, it’s just...\n"
"\n"
"Sometimes I wish I could leave all this behind\n"
"\n"
"Just you and me\n"
"\n"
"Somewhere where nobody knows us\n"
"\n"
"Free from responsibilities\n"
"\n"
"Forever</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3915
msgid "Do you think our people will ever find peace again, Elynia?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Galas
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3939
msgid "It doesn’t matter now, I guess."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3968
msgid "Because I am dead."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3989
msgid "Previous Objective:"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3990
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:3992
msgid "Kill Argan, the Master of Darkness, and put an end to his sinister rule over Irdya"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4008
msgid "What is this place... Something feels amiss."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4053
msgid "Elynia! Oh, I’m so glad I could finally find you... Come with me, this way! Quickly!"
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is Elyssa's voice or thoughts -- unclear which one.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4085
msgid ""
"<i>Why...\n"
"\n"
"Why am I...\n"
"\n"
"What did you do to me...\n"
"\n"
"My body...\n"
"\n"
"The intense red sun...\n"
"\n"
"It’s blinding me...\n"
"\n"
"Please make it stop...\n"
"\n"
"Please...\n"
"\n"
"I just want to go...\n"
"\n"
"I just want to die...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4116
msgid "My hair gets so messy with all the wind in this desert. It’s almost tempting to shave it... Do you think I would look too weird if I did that?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4127
msgid "Did we... Didn’t we have this conversation already?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4132
msgid "I’m just concerned that you might not like it if I do that... Your hair is always so fluffy and nice and beautiful..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4137
msgid "... All right, that is not something I recall you saying..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. [message]: speaker=Argan
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4152
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4163
msgid "You promised..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4217
msgid "I must find Elyssa. She must be here, somewhere..."
msgstr ""

#. [_journeylog_ui_ats_e3s9]
#. This is Zhangor, addressing Elynia and Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4236
msgid ""
"Do you really think you can escape me?\n"
"\n"
"The grasp of Existence permeates all\n"
"\n"
"Your lives\n"
"\n"
"Your aspects\n"
"\n"
"Your souls\n"
"\n"
"They now belong\n"
"\n"
"<big><big>to me</big></big>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Elyssa speaking here.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4284
msgid "<i>Did you know that this entire land used to be a huge empire?</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Elyssa speaking to Argan here.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4297
msgid "<i>You’re asking too much from me. To confront a goddess who has accrued enough power to wipe out an entire world...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Elyssa speaking to Argan here.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4308
msgid "<i>... I understand. </i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Callback to IftU S23Bx.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4352
msgid "<i>... you betrayed... me...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. Callback to IftU S23Bx.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4404
msgid "Argan! No, no, this can’t be happening, you can’t be doing this, I am trying to heal you, don’t you see? I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4423
msgid "Why don’t you say anything? Argan!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia2
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4428
msgid "Argan— No..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4446
msgid "Elyssa?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4457
msgid "YOU KILLED HIM!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4466
msgid "Elyssa, I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4473
msgid "Why— Why do you have to show me this again? WHY?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4536
msgid "Why couldn’t you <b>save</b> him instead?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4574
msgid "WHY?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4605
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) You are a disgrace to your sad excuse of a civilization!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4611
msgid "Stop it... please... Zhangor is attempting to control you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4620
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) Nobody can control me!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4629
msgid "... please..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4637
msgid "... I know you—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4646
msgid "... I know you loved Argan too."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4661
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) ... He wanted you to find me... and guide me... didn’t he...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4671
msgid "... You... you are not me. Why am I crying?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4680
msgid "... Are these... my own tears?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4685
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) ... Try to remember... that you...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4694
msgid "<i>... that I was once...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4704
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) ... human—</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4711
msgid "No... no..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4716
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) Uria demanded I kill them! It was... it was never my intention... please!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4730
msgid "Zhangor is trying to make us lose control..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. This is part of one of Elyssa's lines from IftU scenario 22B.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4736
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) Now that I have failed, there’s no purpose left for me...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4744
msgid "... He is trying to take us both at once... using the powers of the Gatekeeper..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4749
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) Why... why did you bring me back to life... WHY?!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Callback to AtS E3S8A "Interim".
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4758
msgid "<i>... you have allowed others to distort your identity...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. [case]
#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4763
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/10_Blood.cfg:2628
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:12
#: After_the_Storm/macros/character-defines.cfg:27
msgid "Mal Keshar"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4773
msgid "<i>... take the Sceptre of Fire... and wield it... against our enemies...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4781
msgid "... He is using the powers of the Gatekeeper of Urvatha to tear into our minds... I should have known that he would try to do this..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4794
msgid "<i>(metallic voice) Elynia, grab my hand!</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4827
msgid ""
"I could barely tell our memories and emotions apart; it was almost as though our minds had merged into one.\n"
"\n"
"Never in my entire life did I imagine I would be forced by an enemy to share the essence of my self with someone who was previously intent on my destruction; someone who must have already peered countless times without consent. And yet, knowing she had unbounded access to the totality of my experiences did not bother me like it normally would.\n"
"\n"
"I did not need to communicate anything with words, and I knew she would know and understand, and I knew she felt the same; for I was brought to an open door, and she offered — no, <i>needed</i> me to come inside.\n"
"\n"
"And thus I found out that behind all the barriers the demoness meticulously built and kept up all these years, concealed within her warped mortal frame, buried deep inside the core of her usurped divinity, lay a young human girl that was just as afraid of our reality as the rest of us."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4835
msgid ""
"I sensed her fear of Uria, and her fear of the many creatures she had tortured and slain, both under the goddess’ command, and of her own volition; her fear of Zhangor; her fear of failure; her fear of ceasing to exist, tethering her to the prolonged torture that became her new unwanted existence.\n"
"\n"
"I saw a life of loneliness given direction and purpose by the search for knowledge; a fire mage wandering the desolate sands amidst the ruins of Wesnoth; an ambush laid by agents of the so-called Guardian of Life.\n"
"\n"
"I felt the gruesome wounds carved into her very soul by those human-looking monsters before Argan rescued her from their senseless cruelty; the intense pain that welcomed her back into the physical realm as she was forcefully remade into an artificial god; the centuries of hiding behind an invisible mask to protect her fragile self from the corruption rooted deep within the energy hearts of our kind; the soul-crushing agony upon finding out that the one person to whom she had entrusted her humanity was gone for good."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4841
msgid ""
"I caught a glimpse of one her nightmares, one in which she is alone wandering an endless void with nothing in sight but a tree above; a broken tree, in flames.\n"
"\n"
"But it was a tree unlike any other I have never seen..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. Callback to AtS E1S9.3 "The Triad, part 3".
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4853
msgid "<i>Don’t you see? We aren’t that different after all.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elynia
#. Callback to AtS E3S8C "Breakdown".
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4913
msgid "Why... did you not kill me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4922
msgid "Because..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4931
msgid "Argan asked me to help you."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4938
msgid "I could restrain myself no longer. With tears in my eyes I laughed maniacally like I never had before."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4940
msgid "Was that my own emotion, or Elyssa’s? Did it actually matter?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4942
msgid ""
"There was only one thing I knew for sure.\n"
"\n"
"Galas, Anlindë, and Mal Keshar woke me to save Irdya from Uria’s corrupting influence. Their lives were cut short not by Elyssa, but by the broken creature into which Uria turned her."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4946
msgid ""
"I gave Ergea a chance because that is what my friends would have done, and she led me to Elyssa.\n"
"\n"
"If fate dictates we join forces in spite of our mutual enmity, then so be it."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4950
msgid ""
"No-one on Irdya will ever see peace again for as long as Zhangor and Uria exist.\n"
"\n"
"No matter the consequences... no matter who is at my side, I will confront those two.\n"
"\n"
"Uria has to be stopped."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Elyssa
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/09_Dark_Depths.cfg:4985
msgid "... I give up. You are beyond useless."
msgstr ""

