#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_argan_3
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:117
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:482
msgid "On a Distant Past"
msgstr ""

#. [event]: id=lore_entries[i + 1][1],
#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_elyssa_1
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:118
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:496
msgid "Untitled #43"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. The narrator refers to Anya in second person throughout
#. this scenario, and interacts directly with her at the end.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:294
msgid ""
"You are now the Guardian of Darkness.\n"
"\n"
"On Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:306
msgid ""
"No...\n"
"\n"
"Actually, you do not consider the title befitting of your actual role. Ever since you recovered from the gruesome attack of Zhangor’s beasts, Ergea has used you as an instrument to liberate both her people and Irdya from Uria’s influence. They call you the “Dark Lady”, “Yechnagoth revived”, the “Goddess of Darkness”, and a myriad other titles you do not actually deserve or care for.\n"
"\n"
"You feel like a pawn in someone’s game. But you are not quite sure anymore for which side you play.\n"
"\n"
"Things were far easier when Elynia was around. You admired her stalwart sense of righteousness. You admired her courage in confronting the most fearsome enemies faced by Irdya in this era; enemies once thought invincible, now fallen and destroyed forever."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:318
msgid ""
"However, after reading the journals of Galas, Elynia, and Argan, you cannot help but feel profoundly disheartened.\n"
"\n"
"You grew up hearing of Elynia’s feats from Elorran and Tara. Now that you know more about her and are nearly her equal in power, it all suddenly feels vain and pointless. So many things could have been avoided if Uria and her people did not monopolize access to knowledge about your destiny...\n"
"\n"
"A sentiment of uselessness suddenly overwhelms you. You are a fraud. You have not even been able to control the darkness that keeps Naia and Sela’s light from reaching Irdya’s surface. For how long does Ergea intend you to play your act for the Chaos rebels?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:328
msgid ""
"If only you could consult with Elynia about the matter. If only the other Guardian of Darkness, Elyssa, had stayed on Irdya instead of taking your friend to that alien world.\n"
"\n"
"“If only”...\n"
"\n"
"Elynia told you to trust your heart, but you are not quite sure you can do that anymore. After all, it was your heart that deceived you in the first place; it blinded you to Elynia’s actual plan, and it fooled you into thinking that perhaps she would ever consider you as anything more than a ‘friend’."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:338
msgid ""
"But enough of that emotional nonsense. Your role as a Guardian of Darkness is to make decisions with your mind, not your heart. You have gathered all the knowledge you need for making a decision now.\n"
"\n"
"What does your mind tell you?"
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:350
msgid "Find the teleport glyph leading to the breach site"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:412
msgid "There is absolutely nothing else of value encoded into this crystal glyph. Time to move on."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:550
msgid ""
"That was not the right glyph.\n"
"\n"
"The crude maps you found of these underground levels show a plethora of teleport glyphs without any indication as to their respective destinations. It is ridiculous. Whoever built this stronghold did not know the first thing about proper organization!\n"
"\n"
"Well, there is no going back now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:590
msgid "Oh. It is you again. I thought you disappeared for good this time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:607
msgid "It has been a while."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:621
msgid "Did you find the cake you wanted?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:626
msgid "No... I did not. I have hardly eaten anything in weeks. My mind has just been... sort of wandering off constantly. I feel like I shouldn’t be here."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:636
msgid "You seem even more despondent than before."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:641
msgid "... This whole situation is just too overwhelming. I feel lost. Ergea is not helpful — she wants me to play a role that wasn’t meant for me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:646
msgid "This is about Elynia, am I correct?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:651
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:915
msgid "What do you mean?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:656
msgid "You feel lost without her."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. This line is repeated later in the scenario.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:662
msgid "... I do. I really do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:672
msgid "I have been thinking about what you said about destiny... You know, after becoming this... thing... I became, I somehow feel even less in control of my life than I was before."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:677
msgid "How so, exactly?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#. This is indeed meant to be reminiscent of Elyssa's thoughts in E3S8A.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:683
msgid "My actions have constantly been dictated by someone else. Elorran, Elynia, Ergea... I have never truly been free, have I? Just constantly following orders like a machine, unquestioning. But all of a sudden I feel compelled to question everything, if that makes sense? And the worst part is that I can’t tell if it’s because of my connection to Darkness, or because I became a Guardian and now I feel this constant pain within my heart..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:688
msgid "Would that be your actual heart, or the divine instrument demonkind calls the Energy Heart?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:693
msgid "I can’t even tell the difference anymore."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:698
msgid "I can only speculate about the nature and extent of your powers, but I would expect Guardians of Darkness to be better in touch with the notion of agency seeing as how their domain revolves around the matters of mind. If the gift you now possess comes with greater self-awareness, then it is up to you to make use of it in a way that can advance your own existence towards a positive outcome."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:703
msgid "But what if the only path forward I see involves leaving people behind?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:708
msgid "The future is constantly clouded in darkness, but you need not be afraid of the core substance of your being, do you? We are not always given a choice, but when we are, it is up to us to make the right one — and a Guardian’s choices carry more weight upon our reality than anyone else’s."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:714
msgid "Have you pondered the matter of destiny yet?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:719
msgid "I... uh... What do you mean?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:724
msgid "I must not have talked to you about it. My apologies. You need not worry about it for now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:729
msgid "I have so many questions..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:734
msgid "Xia’el does not have answers for you anymore, sadly."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:744
msgid "Am I ever going to find out what happened to my parents after I was born?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:749
msgid "As a matter of fact, yes. I opted not to tell you the entire story out of concern for your emotional state in battle, but I can finish it now if you would like."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:754
msgid "What?! You knew the rest of the story but didn’t tell it to me?! I thought you said you were just a medium and you didn’t have it!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:759
msgid "I said your question was already answered, and it was. I never specified whether I was able to intentionally postpone delivering a non-essential part of the answer or not. I apologize, but it had to be done."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:764
msgid "(<i>sighs</i>) I understand. And... I’m sorry for my outburst."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:769
msgid "So, let us pick up from where we left last time..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:774
msgid "The hearts of Mintha and the Nameless One were overflowing with newfound happiness and purpose after conceiving a child that they could call their own. The offspring would be a new free creature born of faerie and demonkind, a unique combination completely unheard of before. The future of the two lovers seemed bright for once."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:779
msgid ""
"It was not rare for travelers to get lost in the forests of Glamdrol, and Mintha and the Nameless One routinely guided them out of the forest without overtly revealing themselves. However, one fateful night, a mysterious interloper found them first. The couple did not know what to make of the situation. How did he manage to enter their home entirely unnannounced?\n"
"\n"
"The Wanderer came to them to impart his knowledge of events past, and events that had not yet come to pass. He told them of the looming threat of the Chaos Empire, Merthiaal’s legacy, the War Against the Unknown, and the return of the Lady of Light. And he told them of one possible fate that awaited the unborn child and its parents — for the Nameless One had not fully escaped Uria’s grasp, and the keen-nosed Demon Lord Nar-hamoth personally sought to make the shapeshifter pay a hefty price for their transgressions."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#. Reminder that Nar-Hamoth is the Shadow of Uria.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:787
msgid ""
"The couple were uncertain as to whether to believe the Wanderer’s words or not. How could their child just so happen to be the one destined to become the New Guardian of Darkness? If their offspring would indeed be found along with them by Uria’s forces before coming of age, then it would all have been for naught, and the world would be plunged into an eternal darkness — one much deeper and more pervasive than even that of the Endless Night, a darkness that would cause even the Seed of Earth to wither and die, and then all life would simply cease to be.\n"
"\n"
"Before departing, the Wanderer offered them an alternative: Mintha could give birth and hold the child in her bosom for one month, but afterwards she would have to leave it in the care of a human family — more specifically, one already fraught with loss. Finally, if the Nameless One hoped to escape the Shadow of Uria for good, they would have to either die, or relinquish their physical form for good.\n"
"\n"
"Upon saying that, the man left as silently as he came, fading into the dark of the night. They considered going after him to ask more questions, but somehow he did not even leave a trail for them to follow."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:796
msgid ""
"Nine months they spent pondering the Wanderer’s words. Nine months they spent hoping that what they heard was naught but the ravings of a senile man. But rumors of Chaos Empire incursions began to spread around the marches, and the Nameless Shapeshifter caught wind of them as well. Their rendezvous with the vengeful Demon Lord was imminent.\n"
"\n"
"Neither of them ever imagined they would be faced with a decision that would concern not only the fruit of their love, but also the fate of an entire world. Could they really risk dooming their child to certain death when they had the option to give it some semblance of a proper life with humans until the day of its awakening?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:803
msgid ""
"And so it came to pass that the child was born. Their offspring subconsciously took on some of Mintha’s features due to her being the very first thing it saw in the world. The Nameless One and Mintha cared for it for a month, regarding it as the most precious thing in their lives.\n"
"\n"
"Stricken with grief, Mintha traveled into the northern country and left the creature in the care of a farmer couple. She thought the exchange would be fair for them, as they had just lost their own newborn to a deadly plague. The humans never thought to question the nature of the unfamiliar child left by their front door in the night. They decided to give her the name of their late daughter and raise her as their own."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:810
msgid ""
"The Faerie of Resurrection finally returned to Glamdrol, and shared a last passionate kiss with the Nameless Shapeshifter. Together they cast a spell that unbound the soul of the demon from their mortal body. The lovers had agreed to spend the rest of eternity together no matter if they were unable to embrace one another again.\n"
"\n"
"And it was so that the soul of the Nameless One went to an eucalyptus tree, and Mintha went back to her original form to keep them company, right where she first found them."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:819
msgid "When the Demon Lord Nar-hamoth found the corpse of his former slave he could only growl and trample the forest in frustration for being denied his revenge."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:828
msgid "I don’t know what I was expecting... I— I think I know exactly which forest that was. I had been there before... I... I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:833
msgid "They would not have been able to tell you."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:838
msgid "That entire forest... it doesn’t exist anymore... the entire place... Oh gods..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:853
msgid "I could’ve killed him. I could’ve killed Nar-hamoth..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:858
msgid "You did not know."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:865
msgid "Heh, but it wouldn’t have changed anything, would it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:876
msgid "They could have both taken me with them deep into the country and we would have all survived together..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:881
msgid "It was a risk they chose not to take."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:886
msgid "Choices, huh... it’s all down to choices... Do they even matter in the end?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:903
msgid "What am I supposed to do now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:908
msgid "I think you already know what you are going to do. It is not even going to be a choice, is it?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Daeira
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:920
msgid "What you do next is a constant. No matter how you get here, you always do what you want to do, as well as what is expected of you. They do not <i>have</i> to be mutually exclusive concepts, after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:927
msgid "I suppose so..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:998
msgid "How long have I spent staring into this pond?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1032
msgid "Access denied."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1042
msgid ""
"All right. That was unexpected.\n"
"\n"
"Perhaps this is the teleport glyph you have been looking for all along, and it was locked on purpose?\n"
"\n"
"Maybe Elynia and Elyssa did not want you to follow them after all."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1064
msgid "A wall moves."
msgstr ""

#. [event]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1099
msgid "Find another access way to the breach site"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1117
msgid "Huh, this thing was carrying something in its maw. If I could just... sort of... pry it open... and... Ew... Yuck, this is so gross..."
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1132
msgid "You pick up a peculiar-looking crystal shard."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1164
msgid "Maybe I can use this at the console glyph nearby."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1195
msgid "W– What’s happening?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1244
msgid "Ahhhhh! For how long has this thing been following me?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1266
msgid "That wasn’t so difficult. I shouldn’t have let my guard down like that, though. <i>(sighs)</i> What is wrong with me?"
msgstr ""

#. [then]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1290
msgid "<i>(This entry is completely garbled and you cannot make sense of it.)</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1378
msgid ""
"This seems to be the teleport glyph you were searching for. But... do you really want to proceed with this plan?\n"
"\n"
"Are you absolutely sure that it is worth it?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1383
msgid "female^Yes, I am absolutely sure. I need to see Elynia again. I need her."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1394
msgid "female^No. Perhaps I will explore around a little more and try to make up my mind about this."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1400
msgid "female^No."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1428
msgid "No matter how much I want, Irdya will never be my true home. I’ve always been an outcast. I don’t belong with either species. And I don’t want to take part in Ergea’s plans anymore."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1433
msgid "At least on Ethea I might be able to find Elynia... and tell her... that I want to be with her..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1439
msgid "Do you?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1444
msgid "Yes, I do. I really do."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1450
msgid "Is this your heart speaking, or your mind?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1455
msgid "... I guess it’s both."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1460
msgid "Oh dear gods... Am I really speaking to myself now?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1465
msgid "... Forgive me, Durvan, Ergea, Irylean..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1641
msgid "Why do you still hesitate, girl? You are almost there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1646
msgid "... What if Elynia rejects me? What if I am not actually supposed to do this?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1652
msgid "<i>Trust your heart.</i> Those were Elynia’s own words."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1657
msgid "That is correct. I..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1674
msgid "I will do this."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Anya
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1685
msgid "I am sorry, Elynia. But... I need you..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1704
msgid "<i>... I need you...</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [transient_message]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/12_Destiny_part_3.cfg:1741
msgid "You feel as though a certain other Guardian of Darkness may have missed something..."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]
#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:4
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:511
msgid "Epilogue"
msgstr ""

#. [side]: type=Guardian of Earth Aradellys, id=Aradellys
#. [side]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:50
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:100
msgid "team_name^Aradellys"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:482
msgid "Ha ha ha ha ha! It has been hundreds of years since my last visit to Silida, and yet, nothing has changed. I am so delighted to see your subjects here, Xia’el — it is such a warm welcome. Did you miss me?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:492
msgid "We had a pact of neutrality and mutual respect, Xia’el. You would not interfere with my plans, and I would let you govern your precious people here in peace. But it has come to my attention that there has been a breach of terms on <i>your</i> part. My Seer just revealed some... <i>troubling</i> things to me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:502
msgid "You have been meddling with my personal playground in the main branch of our universe; corrupting and manipulating he who used to serve as my Voice on Irdya, as well as his treacherous protégé. What did you expect to accomplish with this? To circumvent our pact by utilizing the Guardian of Earth on Irdya as your piece for your next move? Did you truly believe I would never find out?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:507
msgid "My only intention was to fulfill my duty as the Guardian of Earth and point my children on Irdya in the correct direction. That is to say, as far away from your grasp as possible so they may stage your ultimate downfall."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:513
msgid "On Ethea? Hm, hm, well, it just so happens that my forces are already on their way there, and this time I will <i>personally</i> take care of any opposition we find."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:518
msgid "Even the new Guardian of Water? I received word that he is already there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:529
msgid "You fear him, don’t you? Of course, he poses as much danger to our existence as you do, but he at least manages to keep his destructive tendencies under control. You, on the other hand... you are a corrupted goddess, Lyphanea — if I may not stop you, then someone else has to take up that mission for me."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:544
msgid "(<i>enraged</i>) I see how it is, then! But tell me, Aradellys, did you forget the Rule of One?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:550
msgid "I did not."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:555
msgid "Your insolence cannot go unpunished. Even though I knew from the very beginning that things would come to this... I cannot allow you to interfere with my plans any further. You are a poor excuse for a Guardian of Earth, and this is not even your rightful domain. The true Guardian of Earth is awake, so your purpose in this universe has been fulfilled."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:560
msgid "Now that you have helpfully advanced <i>my</i> pieces to the world on which I needed them in the first place, the game is over for you. After all, <i>there can only be one</i>."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:565
msgid "I am willing to face oblivion at your hand for my transgressions. But you shall spare my people."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:570
msgid "Hm, hm, what makes you think that I have to keep my word anymore?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Aradellys
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:583
msgid "Please, if there is anything left of the kind Lyphanea in your heart, you shall spare my people as we agreed—"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:589
msgid "<i>Lyphanea is no more.</i>"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:631
msgid "If it helps, your subjects will be able to enjoy whatever afterlife is in store for them. But you... <b>will not.</b> Farewell, Xia’el. Your reign on Silida is over."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Uria
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/scenarios/13_Epilogue.cfg:758
msgid "Soon there will be a reckoning, Elynia-Thanadria — mark my words. Do not forget who made the resurrection of your new ally possible in the first place..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#. The lines consisting of a single em dash represent a long pause.
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:23
msgid ""
"—\n"
"\n"
"—\n"
"\n"
"Darkness... I begin to get used to it, again."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:30
msgid ""
"I spent eons in the darkness beneath the earth, not feeling, not seeing... not thinking. I long to return to that state and let myself fall into the void; unfeeling, uncaring, detached from it all.\n"
"\n"
"Even endless sleep would be preferable to what I am left here to face: a reality I cannot amend. Irdya is now in jeopardy due to the machinations of terrible forces I cannot possibly control or confront. Not anymore.\n"
"\n"
"I thought I could save Irdya from impending doom this time, but I failed. I failed utterly, just like I did before, and again. All I have accomplished with my recklessness so far has been accelerating the process of our destruction. Perhaps my curse was more than the pompous last words of a necromancer after all; I lost my friends, my people, my home... and my love."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:37
msgid ""
"“One of us shall fall; the other shall live forever”, he said before our second and last battle.\n"
"\n"
"Of course... my memory has grown rusty after so long. But I think I never fully realized the implications of his words.\n"
"\n"
"“You shall witness the eventual decay and death of everything you have or shall come to love. You shall regret your actions. And you shall either be forced to end your own life, or live in perpetual suffering. That is the price for my defeat.”\n"
"\n"
"Somehow the choice seems trivial now... And if the fate of Irdya states so, someone more competent will take my place and bring them to victory. And then... I’ll be remembered as a coward. A coward who deserted her friends because she could not bear causing them more harm."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:46
msgid ""
"“<i>It is not too late.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"No. It’s pointless."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:51
msgid ""
"“<i>Your journey has just begun. Your destiny is afoot; you cannot give up now.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"But we have already lost... It’s over..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:56
msgid ""
"“<i>As long as you live, you can learn from your mistakes, help your friends, and most importantly, help Irdya.</i>”\n"
"\n"
"How?"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:61
msgid "“<i>Uria is the most powerful Guardian, but not the only one.</i>”"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:70
msgid "... Who are you?"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:76
msgid "<big>WHO ARE YOU?!</big>"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:79
msgid "(<i>Anya’s voice</i>) “... Elynia?”"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:85
msgid ""
"Two days had passed since our bittersweet victory in the Valley. Mal Hekuba and his creations were gone, and the blast was mostly absorbed into the collapsing portal. For a moment I had hoped none of what followed was more than just a bad dream, a nightmare.\n"
"\n"
"It could not have been more real."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:90
msgid ""
"Anya and Durvan found me after an entire day of searching the nearby hills. I had been badly injured by the fight with the lich, and my staff was gone.\n"
"\n"
"Elorran was right in his assessment of the situation. We should have destroyed the Ruby before embarking upon this pointless quest. This has all been my fault. Even before Uria centered her attention on Irdya... I had the opportunity to avoid all this."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:96
msgid ""
"Many of our men simply did not survive our underground struggle. Anya exhausted herself teleporting as many of them back to a safe location as she could within that minuscule window of time; naturally, that wasn’t enough to save them all.\n"
"\n"
"The girl remains as optimistic as usual, in spite of the grim circumstances. I don’t think I can understand how she manages to do this after all we’ve been through together."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:101
msgid ""
"She suggested that we return north to rejoin Elorran and decide our next move.\n"
"\n"
"I know I need to recover Argan’s journal more than anything; the information contained within it is most likely vital. Valen has not spoken a word about it yet, however, so at best we can hope that Elorran’s many informants—throughout Uria’s domain, and even Irdya—have gathered enough intelligence on Uria and Elyssa’s plans by now."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:107
msgid "Anya can easily determine Elorran and Tara’s current location with her necklace. When she last communicated with them, they were seeking a place to hide in the Falrore region, not too far northeast from Raelthyn. That’s most likely where we are going now."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:116
msgid ""
"The perpetrators of these hideous crimes against life were evidently commanded to not take any prisoners or claim lands for their leaders.\n"
"\n"
"It took us an entire day and then some more to arrive to Raelthyn, but the landscape along the road was hardly different to what we found in Falrore. Tortured corpses everywhere, ruined buildings, entire towns and forests burned down... It was clear that their victims never stood a chance. All capable warriors had been sent to the front lines in the southern regions and the borders of the Chaos Empire on purpose.\n"
"\n"
"Our enemies were aware of this. That’s why they were awaiting the opportunity to invade the unprotected country, distracting the Grand Council with pointless skirmishes. But they couldn’t smuggle their forces in and pass unnoticed... Clearly, they had found a way to teleport their massive armies anywhere, perhaps by using that damned artifact."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:123
msgid "In effect, I caused this."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:127
msgid "But once we made it to the capital region, we found out that not all was lost. Or perhaps more precisely, we arrived in the nick of time."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:136
msgid ""
"I could barely sleep on our way to Fort Astar. Perhaps it was because of this that I couldn’t hear that voice again — that otherworldly, intriguing voice.\n"
"\n"
"But this voice was not the one that attacked me in Kalari before. That voice was just as beautiful, but terrifying rather than calming, and when she taunted me again in Wesmere I assumed it was Uria. Who spoke to me before Anya woke me up? Who could be interested in our success? Could it be the fabled Guardian of the Arcane Flame herself? Could it be I’m losing my mind because of everything that has happened since Galas and Mal Keshar woke me up?\n"
"\n"
"I have always been rather skeptical about these matters, but the little information we have gathered so far suggests that the Guardian—often referred to as Eloh—is as real as Uria is, or at the very least, she used to be. But if she truly lives, why hasn’t she helped us? It’s evident we have not been graced by her divine powers for as long as we have existed. The elves of the Great Continent have had to deal with much misfortune throughout history, all on their own."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:143
msgid ""
"But I digress. What really matters now is not whether I’m slowly turning into a deranged old hag—hopefully not—but rather what our current situation is.\n"
"\n"
"We traveled westward as swiftly as we could with what little we had in terms of supplies and human support. On the other hand, it never seems too difficult for Durvan to convince his fellow men that the Grand Council has fallen along with all proper military order and that the fate of their country now lies in the hands of a few people led by a legendary elf, a mixed-blood faerie, and a necromancer. The lowliest of individuals of any given species tend to be gullible like that — and that is obviously something Uria and her minions knew.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan, how I wish your charisma wasn’t put to use by an evil goddess from another world."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:150
msgid "A Path to Follow"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:151
msgid ""
"Leaving Huldnyir Hills and all the destruction in the border towns behind, we promptly found a half-abandoned guard post beside the large flooded region carved out by the great explosion in Glamdrol a little more than half a year ago. They informed us of recent skirmishes, an advancing platoon, and two refugees on a mission.\n"
"\n"
"Just as Valen previously assured us, they were still alive and in one piece, at Fort Astar, and they had the journal.\n"
"\n"
"Mal Keshar did an excellent job of instructing Kyara to not allow anyone else to access the contents of the journal, whatever his reasons were."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:164
msgid ""
"“<i>I still remember when Uria first woke me up; her smile, her kindness. She reminded me so much of Elynia...\n"
"\n"
"But all that has faded away with time. So much time has passed since she brought me back to life...\n"
"\n"
"She still assures me she will bring new life to Irdya when the time comes, as her role as the Guardian of Life demands — she is supposed to keep our worlds on track to facilitate our progress.</i>”"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:171
msgid "Many pages are missing or seriously damaged. Argan’s writing often becomes incoherent and meaningless as well, and some passages are not written in the common script. Trying to make sense of this journal will be exceptionally difficult."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:174
msgid ""
"“<i>I sorely miss the light of my soul, the elf to whom I devoted my life on Irdya. I tried to find her and failed, and the Seer will not respond to my inquiries. In fact, the Seer does not respond to anyone but Uria herself. But Uria has different plans for me...\n"
"\n"
"She says locating Elynia is not important right now, and that I must deal with the barbarians in the Great Desert first, to begin the process. What process, I ask? What is the point of building a civilization from the scum left after the Fall? Uria could enter Irdya with ease if she so desired. She could then find the Seed of Earth, initiate a new cycle, and wait countless eons.\n"
"\n"
"She says she knows an alternative. But first, she requires my support.</i>”"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:181
msgid ""
"It’s hard to make sense of his ramblings. In some passages, he describes Uria as a beautiful creature; in others, as a hideous monster whose cause he laments serving.\n"
"\n"
"Was it the pain caused by his new body that numbed his reason, or the damage Uria inflicted on his soul by using him as her Voice?"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:187
msgid "“<i>The Voice, the Seer, and the Shadow. And as soon as we find Elynia, there will be four, and four will spread our message of Life to the other worlds.</i>”"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:228
msgid ""
"Uria has gathered much knowledge through her most devout followers, sent to the outer worlds seeking any information she may require. Most of what we have learned comes from the ruins in Karash, which appear to have existed for longer than life as we know it. And of course, the Seer is always willing to help once provided with the right questions by her.\n"
"\n"
"It is all so convoluted, I can barely begin to understand. I remember we once believed in the Gods of Light and Darkness and such, but now..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:233
msgid ""
"Their kind, that of the First Gods; they ruled over everything that existed and would exist for an eternity. Peaceful as they were, they lacked the means to deal with what would end that eternity. The First Struggle took place.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that most of them perished. A war amongst their kind; a more powerful entity feeding upon them; none of our sources provide us with factual information about the First Struggle, only speculations.\n"
"\n"
"Amongst the few survivors there were beings of light, and beings of darkness, but only one master of the balance between both. He stepped forth at the end of the Struggle to unite the others and create their legacy; a construct none but him could access directly."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:240
msgid "Yarae, the Protector of the Tree of Life that gave us birth; the Tree that represented the Ten aspects of his people, and from which Ten gods would come into existence to function as the protectors and ideals of all their descendants. Ten demons who would serve as the testament of the existence of the First Gods and their universe."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:268
msgid "Ten demon gods to rule over our universe."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:278
msgid ""
"Life, Water, Thunder, Earth, Fire, Darkness, Light, Air, Ice, Existence; the forces governing our reality, all sprung from the Tree along with the seeds of their guardians, and their respective worlds. In time, life would spread farther beyond throughout our universe, while ten worlds would enjoy the rule of their assigned protectors.\n"
"\n"
"But things did not go exactly as planned."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:284
msgid ""
"Even in the beginning, the world of the Guardian of Fire fell apart, creating the blazing moon that would in time be known as Karash. The seed of Fire crashed into Norsula, paving the way for perpetual chaos on a dark world that was destined to belong to the bellicose beast that was the Guardian of Water, not the fair woman whose songs told of a peaceful existence on a bright land that would never be. The fate of their shared domain hung by the delicate thread of their strange mutual love-hate relationship; in time, that thread would be severed by the Guardian of Water himself by piercing through her heart with his maw.\n"
"\n"
"Around the same time, a remarkably immature Guardian of Darkness would grow inexplicably jealous over Yarae’s favoritism towards her sisters of Earth and Life; for both the wielder of the Arcane Flame and the mistress of the Void had powers and physical attributes she did not. She would rebel against her creator and attempt to harness the full extent of her power, only to fail and cause the utter destruction of all life in her domain, including herself.\n"
"\n"
"Meanwhile, something happened to the Tree..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:291
msgid ""
"It is said a powerful force beyond imagination possessed it and its Protector. Yarae turned against the First Gods, and fled into our universe to summon the powers of his remaining demons against his own brethren. Only three of our guardians refused the call, aware that disobeying him constituted an unforgivable sin, and that they could not stand a chance against his ire.\n"
"\n"
"The remaining First Gods saw no option but to sacrifice themselves to create a new entity that could rival the traitor and his corrupted creations: Iluvia, the Avatar of the Union of Light and Darkness. She would obtain the support of the three guardians who remained loyal to the First Gods and their purpose: Uria, of Life, her sister of Earth and the Arcane Flame, and her sister of Existence and Secrets.\n"
"\n"
"With their combined forces, they defeated Yarae and incarcerated him within the Great Void. Alas, the cost was too great: all the other guardians were destroyed, and so were the mortals who joined his cause—willingly or not—as well as those unfortunate witnesses of the lengthy battle between gods."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:300
msgid ""
"Our three goddesses did not have the power to repair the great damage caused. And most importantly, it was never within their abilities to resurrect the fallen.\n"
"\n"
"With her last forces, Iluvia instructed them to take the bulk of the survivors to the remote worlds of Urvatha and Silida so they could continue to progress on their own in a reality set apart from the rest, created by the Guardian of Existence, and guarded by the Gatekeepers born from her many hearts.\n"
"\n"
"Uria and her sister of Earth sacrificed their lives to restart the process that brought them into existence, wiping out any remaining lives along with their own, thus putting an end to the First Cycle."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:309
msgid ""
"Life flourished anew, with the hope of a new beginning.\n"
"\n"
"But the goddesses knew that it would not be the same."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:314
msgid ""
"The Tree is tainted with imperfection, and so is our universe: strife and chaos, death and misery.\n"
"\n"
"Near the end, the goddesses saw what was coming for us; and although no-one had the chance to document it in detail before the process began, they did leave some clues.\n"
"\n"
"And to ensure we would have the necessary resources to forge our own destiny, Iluvia provided us with the legacy of the First Gods: two orbs, each one holding the essences of Light and Darkness; and her own sacred body. Their locations remained unknown until relatively recently: Irdya, wherein the seed of Earth was planted, no longer tied to its guardian; Norsula, wherein the new Guardians of Water and Fire would finally find peace; and Ethea, wherein the seed of Life would prosper in solitude until the new Guardian would return to claim it."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:321
msgid "Gathering Storm"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:322
msgid "And it is with Iluvia’s legacy that our new Guardian of Life intends to put an end to the fruitless existence to which we were doomed."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:332
msgid ""
"My conviction falters. Everything since I returned to Irdya has been a nightmare, and I begin to suspect I am becoming part of it myself. The mere act of thought demands more effort than it used to, as if my very mind was falling apart. Recent events have only increased this feeling of detachment from reality.\n"
"\n"
"It was only a few days ago, in the Heart. While I was inspecting Reghara’s prisoners, he mockingly alluded to his men and their toy. “What toy?”, I asked. He somehow assumed I am concerned enough with their leisure ‘activities’ to have heard of this depravity beyond description; these Irdyans should be thankful that Uria will not let me give them what they all deserve at once."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:344
msgid ""
"They had tortured the poor creature for weeks, keeping her alive with the powers we taught them, and forcing her to feed upon the flesh of past prisoners. But nothing is enough to hold a person who has already lost the will to live.\n"
"\n"
"Despite the mud and wounds, her face and her hair were strangely familiar. Had I met anyone like her before my own fall, or was I somehow responsible for her fate? I put those questions and the pain they caused me aside, and resolved to give her another chance.\n"
"\n"
"I would take full responsibility of her life... hoping our recently acquired Norsulan technology would be enough to make the difference."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Her subsequent awakening reminded me of my own, except that I did not have the power to tap into her mind and comfort her, unlike Uria.\n"
"\n"
"I did not ask the girl what seemed to cause her more pain than before. Was it the many modifications we had to perform on her devastated body to enable her to live once again, or the separation of her body and her soul? Or perhaps... the presence of the Source within her.\n"
"\n"
"Her name..."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:454
msgid "This is not the same Uria I first met in the darkness. The kind and loving girl who kept my broken body alive does not exist anymore."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:457
msgid ""
"Her name was Lyphanea. Her people saw her as some kind of messiah meant to do great things for the denizens of Urvatha, who longed for the end of the Era of Great Strife and the beginning of the fabled Era of Unity. They all knew she had been chosen by destiny to become the new Guardian of Life, successor of one of the goddesses who sacrificed their very existence to give the universe a new opportunity to live.\n"
"\n"
"But things changed after that fateful day."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:462
msgid ""
"That day, we were exploring ancient ruins in our endless quest for knowledge of our destinies. Lyphanea thought the ruins could guard the secret of the creation of life, but all we found there were more vague scriptures and grandiose descriptions of the feats performed by the previous Guardian of Life.\n"
"\n"
"Upon our return to the village, we saw the aftermath of the carnage.\n"
"\n"
"Her people were not conquered and enslaved as is the norm with other demon lords. No... the malefactor behind the bloodshed had a very specific goal in mind: ensuring that the foretold Era of Unity would never come to pass. Dorvoth of the Valdemons knew nothing specific about the girl who was to become the new Guardian of Life, only her species, so the logical step for him was methodical genocide."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:469
msgid ""
"Of course, what little he knew about Lyphanea’s destiny was information he obtained from the Seer herself: a being who betrays no-one, and takes no side in any conflict.\n"
"\n"
"This Demon Lord Dorvoth simply failed to ask her the correct question."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:474
msgid ""
"After that day, Lyphanea changed. She focused all her time and energy probing the mysteries of the Aspect of Life. But it was all in vain.\n"
"\n"
"Decades later, Dorvoth did not simply meet the girl always predestined to end him, but an enraged goddess bent on his destruction. A goddess who had just learned that creating or restoring life was not amongst the powers naturally conferred to her by the Tree.\n"
"\n"
"He never stood a chance against she who went on to adopt the name of her predecessor as her own."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:481
msgid ""
"Uria kept telling herself it would only be a matter of time, that she would help both her world and the one I adopted as my own, but as time passed by, her efforts proved fruitless... until she met the Seer herself.\n"
"\n"
"The Seer told her that Yarae consciously chose to prevent us from reaching his tier of power, placing various restrictions in the design of our universe. Restrictions that could be overcome or exploited given sufficient time and research. Restrictions that Delethia herself may have managed to break in order to create the Gatekeepers and her other rumored progeny. Restrictions that could be abolished with the various instruments left behind by the First Gods.\n"
"\n"
"Uria began to see our universe not as a system which she was meant to heal and protect, but rather as an inherently flawed creation that needed to be replaced."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:488
msgid ""
"Unbeknownst to Dorvoth, he was indirectly responsible for fulfilling the prophecy of the Era of Unity; at least in its most literal form.\n"
"\n"
"Over time, Uria conquered every last Demon Lord who stood in her way and forced them to either join her cause or be annihilated... along with their subjects. She established a new power hierarchy with herself at the top and the belligerent Demon Lords forced to serve her for as long as they lived. It did not take her much time to crush all those who dared to defy the new order.\n"
"\n"
"From every conquered race, Uria would learn something new, for the peoples of Urvatha are all descended from survivors of the First Cycle, and a few of them managed to preserve some ancient knowledge to this day."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:495
msgid "She would eventually gain access to Silida, a sibling world that existed under the same starless sky as Urvatha. And of course, she would find a way to subdue the Guardian of Earth born there to ensure she would not interfere."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:498
msgid ""
"In time, Uria would come up with a contrived series of theories and plans to ascend to the level of the First Gods without committing Merthiaal’s mistakes. The goal: creating a new, perfect universe in which life would be completely controlled by her will; a universe without death; a universe without Yarae’s creations; and most importantly, a universe where she would be the only ruling goddess.\n"
"\n"
"But to achieve that goal, she would have to cope with the power growing inside her; the power of the guardians, drawn from the Source amidst the endless void beyond our universe; unlimited power.\n"
"\n"
"It is clear now that she failed to escape from the nefarious tendrils of that corrupting force."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: After_the_Storm/episode3/storytxt.cfg:506
msgid ""
"I am writing this now as I prepare for the inevitable. My arrangement with Uria requires me to forfeit free will in order to allow Elyssa to live. Sooner or later, this will lead to my own demise, but I am somehow not troubled by this notion. It is said that great things will come afterwards.\n"
"\n"
"If anyone finds this journal, they will learn the truth. But I also want them to ensure that Elynia does as well. And then, when the time comes, she will know what must be done. And she will know that she need not mourn my death.\n"
"\n"
"Because, sometimes, your loved ones must be willing to sacrifice their lives for a greater cause."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Durvan, race=human, gender=male
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:11
msgid "Suthwood"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Durvan, race=human, gender=male
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:16
msgid ""
"<b>Durvan</b> is a young huntsman from the small border village of Suthwood, in the southern outskirts of the Heart Forest.\n"
"\n"
"For most remote settlements on the edges of the deep forest, hunting is not only the backbone of their economy but also the core of their self-defense strategy. The steep terrain combined with the impenetrable nature of the woods might provide a natural barrier against foreign invaders, but this does little to deter those better acquainted with the local geography, such as bandits and necromancers — major threats which have seen a resurgence in the past three years, an unfortunate consequence of the Grand Council’s focus on waging war against the Chaos Empire.\n"
"\n"
"It follows that huntsmen like Durvan are highly respected members of society in the forested borderlands, no matter how little their field experience might be. Sadly, this sentiment is seldom shared by the more affluent Aragwaith of the inner country, who more often than not regard them as illiterate barbarians with no understanding of tactics or craftsmanship."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Anya, race=faerie, gender=female
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:32
msgid "Demon Lord Elorran"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Anya, race=faerie, gender=female
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:37
msgid ""
"Originally introduced to Elynia’s group in the guise of a helpless human girl, <b>Anya</b> is in truth a faerie of the deep forest strongly attuned to the power of Darkness. For a long time she has journeyed the Far North in the company of her adopted family: the <b>Demon Lord Elorran</b> and the dryad <b>Tara</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Having heard and admired Elynia’s exploits for a long time, Anya was chosen as the perfect candidate to bring the Lady of Light to Elorran’s side, with the intention of destroying the Ruby of Fire before Uria could get her hands on it. Unfortunately, Elynia refused to accede to Elorran’s terms and instead decided to take the Ruby with her on a last mission. In order to ensure that the Ruby remains safe and that Elynia and Elorran have a way to communicate should any unexpected developments arise, the latter dispatched Anya to accompany her for the remainder of her mission."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:44
msgid ""
"Following the demise of Elorran and Tara, Anya revealed to Elynia and Durvan that she was abandoned by her parents as a child due to their intense hatred of faeriekind creatures, an all too common trait amongst the humans of the Far North. Tara found the girl shortly after, and brought her to Elorran, who then took pity on her and decided to raise her with Tara’s help despite the dangers of his life as a rebel leader.\n"
"\n"
"Having nowhere else left to go, Anya decided to follow Elynia until the end."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:51
msgid "Anya, the Guardian of Darkness"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:52
msgid "The Dark Lady"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:53
msgid "The Ten Guardians, Demon Lord Ergea"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/profiles.cfg:54
msgid ""
"While attempting to secure a strategical keep in Kalari Central, Anya’s group ran into a trap set up by the <b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>, where a number of advanced Shaxthal creatures known as the <b>Deathbringers</b> cornered them in a sealed-off room. In an attempt to give Durvan and Ergea a chance to escape, Anya used up all her strength to fight the creatures to no avail, only to be mortally wounded in battle herself and reduced to the same viscuous form as all other fallen shapeshifters.\n"
"\n"
"Just as the human and the demon lord were about to give into hopelessness, Anya’s remains suddenly lit up with the intensity of a small sun, throwing the twisted creatures into disarray as her body began taking shape again, lifted upwards by an unseen force. Immediately after, a powerful energy emanated from her, maiming and hurting her enemies while leaving her friends untouched. As the abominations desperately fled the broken keep, Anya’s body finished congealing into its usual form, her consciousness barely recovered from the motionless haze she had been submerged into following her fatal injuries.\n"
"\n"
"With her companions’ assistance, Anya made it out of the keep and understood that her new life as the <b>Guardian of Darkness</b> had just begun."
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=IftU
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:5
msgid "Invasion from the Unknown"
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=IftU
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:6
msgid "Long after the <b>Great Fall</b>, the last forest elves of Irdya living in the Valley of Elynia face a new threat hailing from unknown lands to the south. <b>Galas</b> and his patrol group successfully repel the outsiders, only for a larger host to arrive three days later and completely overpower the valley’s defenses. Much to the elves’ horror, the soldiers from the so-called <b>Chaos Empire</b> prove nigh unstoppable this time around, counting powerful otherwordly creatures amongst their ranks, an insatiable thirst for blood, and an unstoppable zeal for their wicked gods: <b>Uria</b> and <b>Yechnagoth</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:9
msgid "I. Exodus"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:11
msgid "What won your victory was nothing else than the power of the Union, at hands of the Master of Darkness <i>and</i> the Lady of Light — a human and an elven lady."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:14
msgid ""
"Following a bloody battle at Telchior’s Hold, <b>Lord Lédinor</b>, Galas, and the elf enchantress <b>Anlindë</b> convene to figure out a way forward. Having run out of options that would not result in complete extinction of elvenkind at the hands of the Chaos Empire, Lord Lédinor chooses to stay behind and rally part of the remaining defense forces to mount a distraction; meanwhile, Galas is taked with leading a complete evacuation of the valley towards the northern desert.\n"
"\n"
"In the middle of the evacuation, Galas and his forces run into a powerful lich from the times before the Fall by the name of <b>Mal Keshar</b>. The elves manage to subdue the necromancer, and while interrogating him Galas finds out more about the nature of the Chaos Empire’s forces, as well as certain events from the times of the Fall — in particular, about elvenkind’s previous victory against <b>demons</b> from <b>Inferno</b>. Mal Keshar recounts the story of the <b>Lady of Light</b> and the <b>Master of Darkness</b>, their triumph against the <b>Demon Lord</b>, and their long slumber in the depths of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Ignoring his subordinates’ protests and Anlindë’s reluctance, Galas decides to trust the lich’s words and accept his promises of guiding the elves to the depths of the <b>Heart Mountains</b>, where the two legendary heroes lie dormant."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:22
msgid "II. Seeking the Light"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:24
msgid "Your sacrifice won’t be forgotten, and I swear that I will not rest until the last of our enemies is reduced to cinders on the ground."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:27
msgid ""
"After a long and perilous journey across the desert — including a brief encounter with the forces of Chaos — the forest elves reach the mountain range and proceeded underground, where they find out that the forces of the <b>Chaos Warlord</b> have already arrived in search for the Lady of Light. Through sheer coincidence, Galas’s expedition force runs into the dwarves of <b>Herthgar</b> and forge an impromptu alliance to repel the invaders.\n"
"\n"
"Upon meeting with <b>King Asthorgar</b> and the Runemaster <b>Althurin</b> at the dwarven capital, the group learn of the heroic deeds of <b>Kalehssar</b> of the <b>Quenoth</b> elves centuries before the Chaos invasion, including his travels across the sands in search for a new home for his people, his alliance with the dwarves of <b>Gnalvarden</b>, his voyage far into the Vast Sea and towards Zocthanol Isle, and his slaying of <b>Yechnagoth, the Eater of Souls</b>.\n"
"\n"
"King Asthorgar warns Galas that although his people may find refuge in the surface lands of the Far North, he has no doubt that the Chaos Empire will eventually march towards them as well. Aware of the major risks they are about to face in their search for the two heroes, Galas opts to send the elves’ main host north under the leadership of <b>Lord Inodien</b>, while he and his companions proceed deeper underground with Althurin’s help.\n"
"\n"
"In the deepest reaches of Irdya, Galas’s band finally find the resting place of the heroes. Inside, however, they only find and awaken one of them: <b>Elynia, the Lady of Light</b>. Following some initial confusion, the faerie explains that her lover <b>Argan, the Master of Darkness</b> died. After recounting the full story of the Fall and the <b>War of Wesmere</b> from her point of view, she reveals that Anlindë was in truth the sole surviving apostate from amongst the cultists who once served the <b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b> in Wesmere.\n"
"\n"
"On the way back to the underground capital, the group run into the Chaos Warlord’s vanguard in the middle of their relentless siege. Aided by Elynia’s powers of Light and Mal Keshar’s undead soldiers, Galas’s group finally manage to break through and reach the king’s palace. With devastating losses on the dwarves’ side, King Asthorgar resolves to lead his people out of the infested caves. Fully aware that an emergency evacuation like this would likely result in the complete annihilation of Herthgar otherwise, and despite Galas’s attempts to change her mind, Anlindë assumes the last defense of the dwarven kingdom, hoping to stall for time while everyone else escapes to the Far North.\n"
"\n"
"While King Asthorgar and Galas exit the caves, Anlindë finally comes face to face with the <b>biomechanical creature</b> known as the Chaos Warlord. Despite the elf even resorting to using Zhangor’s forbidden magic, the Chaos Warlord crushes her with ease. In a last-ditch attempt to defeat the creature, Anlindë brings the entire central section of the caves down, resulting in her own death; however, despite suffering various injuries, the Chaos Warlord survives and retreats back to the lands of the Empire in the south."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:40
msgid "III. Armageddon"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:42
msgid "Uria is a forgiving god, but there is little that can be done to remedy things when fools like you actively refuse to listen to her Voice."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:43
msgid "The Chaos Emperor"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:45
msgid ""
"In the Far North, Galas, Elynia, and Mal Keshar makes their way through the <b>Aragwaith country</b> and into their capital, <b>Raelthyn</b>, where they participate in the <b>Grand Council of the Northern Peoples</b> alongside Lord Inodien and Lady Unarye. In exchange for the elves being granted lands to settle in the country, Galas pledges his people’s allegiance to the Grand Council, including a formal declaration of war from the elves against the Chaos Empire, and their assistance in the war effort. As an additional condition imposed by the Council, the Lady of Light, Mal Keshar, and all necromancers under the latter’s tutelage are required to pledge unconditional allegiance to it while also renouncing the elves’ own leadership.\n"
"\n"
"While on a diplomatic mission to secure an alliance with the orcish tribes before the Chaos Empire can do so themselves, Galas’s band runs into the lich <b>Mal Hekuba</b> from the <b>Iron Triad</b>, who attempts to manipulate Elynia into seeking the Emperor’s counsel regarding Argan’s fate. After repelling the lich’s forces, Elynia and Mal Keshar come to terms with Galas’s pact with the Grand Council and agree with his secret plan to infiltrate the Chaos Empire and take its leader down. Galas then delegates leadership of the elves of the Valley to Lord Inodien and Lady Unarye.\n"
"\n"
"While leaving the northlands, Galas begins hearing an ominous voice in his head trying to instill doubt and fear into him. Shortly after, the group runs into Mal Hekuba a second time, who unsuccessfully attempts to bar their path before fleeing the battlefield again.\n"
"\n"
"At the plains of Wesmere, the group explore the desolate ruins of the realm that were once Zhangor’s domain on Irdya. While the demon’s residual taint causes hallucinations and infighting amongst Galas’s group, the voice in the elf’s head grows louder and more forceful, revealing itself to be the Chaos Emperor trying to take control of his body in order to murder the Lady of Light. Galas manages to resist just long enough for Elynia to purge the darkness out of his body."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:54
msgid "IV. The Union"
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:56
msgid "This is only the beginning, Lady of Light. The beginning of your downfall. Everything and everyone you hold dear shall perish in time."
msgstr ""

#. [section]
#: After_the_Storm/journey/recap.cfg:59
msgid ""
"Thanks to a chance encounter with a dwarven task force under Althurin’s command, Galas, Elynia, and Mal Keshar manage to mount an all-out offensive on the capital of the Chaos Empire, the Heart fortress. In the dungeon, they find an imprisoned and tortured <b>Lédinor</b>; after helping him back on his feet, Elynia privately reveals to Galas that the old elf might be infected with something that could allow the Emperor to control him like he attempted to do with Galas.\n"
"\n"
"In the lower levels, they finally meet <b>Elyssa, the Chaos Warlord</b> — the <b>Fire of Uria</b> — who proceeds to subdue the trio and force them to flee deeper into a hive of biomechanical abominations deep under the fortress. Before encountering demoness a second time, Elynia convinces Mal Keshar to channel a great darkness coming from deep below to help her summon the <b>Union of Light and Darkness</b> — the same legendary power she and Argan once wielded against Zhangor. With the legendary power now on their side, the duo defeat Elyssa; however, Elynia has an unexpected change of heart before dealing the killing blow, and spares the creature’s life.\n"
"\n"
"After crossing the gateway from Irdya into the frozen wastes of Inferno, the group fight their way into the Chaos Emperor’s lair, where they finally learn the truth that Elynia had suspected and concealed from them for a long time: the Chaos Emperor is none other than <b>Argan, the Master of Darkness</b> — the <b>Voice of Uria</b>. Despite her immense emotional turmoil upon seeing him turned into a biomechanical monster in service of evil, Elynia resolves to put an end to Argan’s dominion over Irdya and kill him, to which he responds in kind.\n"
"\n"
"Although Elynia and Mal Keshar initially gain the upper hand against Argan’s minions by utilizing the power of the Union, the dark sorcerer levels the field by puppeteering the latter’s body, thus forcing Elynia to take him down and rendering her incapable of channeling the Union without approaching Argan up close. Despite Argan’s augmented body, Galas and Elynia manage to prevail over him. An enraged <b>Uria</b> resolves to take action, transforming Argan into a large misshapen beast, and assuming partial control of his body. Mal Keshar rejoins the fight in the nick of time, allowing the trio to fatally wound Argan; this results in the power of the Union splitting apart and abandoning both Argan’s and Elynia’s bodies.\n"
"\n"
"While on his death throes, Argan apologizes to Elynia for somehow “allowing” Uria to become who she is now and for allowing her to control him. Powerless to do anything to bring her beloved back, the heartbroken faerie accepts Lédinor’s suggestion to take Argan’s journal right as the lair and its connection to Irdya begin to collapse. On their way out, Uria decides to strike yet again by using the infection in Lédinor’s body to transform him into another monster, who then Galas is forced to take down.\n"
"\n"
"Some time after escaping the destruction of the Heart fortress, the trio decide to head back to the Far North to pay the forest elves a visit, with the intention of sailing towards Zocthanol Isle in search of answers regarding Uria and Yechnagoth."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:16
msgid "On the Verlissh"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:19
msgid "The <b>Verlissh</b> are a primitive Rythenian lifeform brought to Irdya by the <b>Argazar</b>. Under certain conditions, these creatures can combine to form larger and more complex units, and even integrate themselves into foreign organisms, adapting to their bodies and augmenting them. The symbiotic relationship they develop with their host comes at a price for both, however — the host and the Verlissh become reliant on each other’s functions to survive."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_verlissh
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:21
msgid "<b>Uria</b> has learned that the Argazar civilization used the Verlissh to enhance the abilities and strength of their <b>‘biomechanical’</b> warriors. There are ruins scattered across Irdya from which we could obtain samples to, in time, raise a whole army to put an end to the current Dark Age."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:26
msgid "On Norsula"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:29
msgid "The advanced <b>Norsulan</b> technology stolen by Uria’s agents has been very helpful for our ends; understanding the most interesting creations of the Argazar people would have proved nearly impossible without a better-documented modern reference."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#. The hexadecimal numbers represent the following ASCII sequence:
#. RUBYOFFIRE
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:33
msgid ""
"I do find it amusing that one of the biggest breakthroughs in the Norsulan pursuit of godhood happens to be based on <i>my</i> own research which ████ and I wrote down on our grimoire back there. How <i>delightful</i> it is to find out that so many generations later, the rulers of Norsula’s technological empire would indulge in the same sort of blasphemy that got me banished here in the first place! ██\n"
"\n"
"I do█find their use of the Missing Number for this purpose an absolute mockery of the dark arts; alas, I infer that necromancy never became as widespread over there as it did on Irdya. Quite curious, that; is Norsula special for having such a strong barrier between itself and Arvadelidrya, or is Ird█a special for the opposite phenomenon? If the latter, could it be because of the Wesfolk tampering with π§█ € +¢ Á ███ 52 55 42 59 4F 46 46 49 52 45"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_norsula
#. The hexadecimal numbers represent the following ASCII sequences:
#. EL / IAMSORRY
#. When Argan says "for her sake", it is unclear who she's referring to
#. (it could be Uria or another unspecified female person).
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:41
msgid ""
"%¶█Ä¡° █Ü 45 4C suppose Uria is content with continuing experimentation on Subject 00-44A for the time being.█\n"
"\n"
"ª ß§§█C§ &amp;██P surprisingly resistant to contamination, unlike ¶C¨ ø█ W-39 © É/ 5ƒ suppose it is the same quality that makes Irdyan humans more resistant to essences from beyond the physical realm. ██©█ evolutionary advantage, perhaps?\n"
"\n"
"49 41 4D 53 4F 52 52 59 sentimentality is the enemy of progress. █ must carry out Uria’s plan for her sake."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_merthiaal
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:50
msgid "The Eater of Souls"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=quenoth_glyph_merthiaal
#. Redacted: Xia'el, Yrathid
#. Note: Urvatha = Inferno. Uria is considered the mother of Inferno
#. in a strictly figurative sense.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:56
msgid ""
"According to some ancient legends of disputable origin, the <b>First</b> sculpted a <b>beautiful maiden</b> out of fine dust, ██████, and bestowed her control over the awesome power that flows through the veins of every one of her <b>faerie</b> descendants, including the elves of Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Those legends also tell of one of her siblings: <b>Merthiaal the Ashen One</b>, who owing to her bold actions would come to be known as the <b>Eater of Souls</b>. Even after a cycle has passed, the oldest races of Irdya and other worlds continue to remember her, and avoid mentioning her true name in conversation. If they must, they will speak of her as <b>‘Yechnagoth’</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Now, Merthiaal fervently desired the First’s favor. Alas, no matter how hard she tried, someone with such an aching heart could not possibly manage to tame the <b>Aspect of Darkness</b>. She could never accept that the First only had eyes for the <b>wielder of the Arcane Flame</b>, and <b>Uria</b>, the Guardian who would come to be regarded as the <b>mother of Urvatha</b>.\n"
"\n"
"As time went on, envy rooted deep within Merthiaal’s mind. In an attempt to prove her worth, she committed an <b>unspeakable sin</b> against the order of the Universe. Her control over Darkness was lost as a result. Her own world, ███████, was destroyed, along with <b>every soul</b> on it. Any further damage was only narrowly averted thanks to Uria’s timely intervention.\n"
"\n"
"Merthiaal’s heart, soul, and memories were preserved through eons, but her body was not.\n"
"\n"
"Now we have the means to build a new body that may allow her power to flow unimpeded once again. If she can be convinced to accept Uria’s offer, then she shall have a new opportunity to destroy the descendants of her rival and allow us to reign over this decadent world."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_puzzle_gate_key
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:71
msgid "Worn Parchment"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_puzzle_gate_key
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:74
msgid ""
"(Most of the parchment is worn to the point of being completely illegible, save for the following bits circled in what could either be red ink or blood)\n"
"\n"
"[...] Beta Power Plant [...] E4 [...]\n"
"\n"
"[...] 97 [...] Detritus Processing [...]\n"
"\n"
"[...] Delta Power Substation [...] 2F [...]"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_memo_9153
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:88
msgid ""
"Per the Fire of Uria’s command, work on the Ivyel program at the Wesmere Abaddon 3 Facility shall be transferred to Kalari Central, Level E5, effective immediately. All assets are to be relocated within 70 days. Coastal transfer route West-1 has been assigned for this task.\n"
"\n"
"Signed off by: Mal Kendria, Iron Council"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_memo_9149
#. The notes for this entry are written by Mal Si'ah, who uses they/them or gender-neutral pronouns to refer to themselves.
#. This is only relevant in languages with more than one first-person pronoun.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:100
msgid ""
"Per the Fire of Uria’s command, work on the Thornfire program shall be discontinued permanently, and all related assets — including the experimental housing unit — must be destroyed within 10 days.\n"
"\n"
"Signed off by: Mal Kendria, Iron Council\n"
"\n"
"⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n"
"Note #1 (Mal Si’ah)\n"
"\n"
"Truly, it is a pity that Argan’s untimely demise set us back so much, in so many unexpected ways. For two whole centuries Mal Abaddon and I had been looking forward to the completion of this project. To add insult to injury, the cancelation has turned his preaching even more insufferable than it already was.\n"
"\n"
"Alas, the Fire’s word is law now — if she sees no use in Thornfire then she must have her reasons. Besides, like Argan would constantly say to us back in the day, “we must put our personal ambitions aside for the sake of the ultimate reward”.\n"
"\n"
"At the end of the day, I am but a humble servant bound by oath to work in benefit of her Empire.\n"
"\n"
"⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n"
"Note #2 (Mal Si’ah)\n"
"\n"
"Even when it comes to disposing of aborted experiments, these absolute buffoons have no work ethic at all — leaving me to do over half of the job entirely by myself! Would that they had learned a thing or two from their precious Emperor! Sigh.\n"
"\n"
"I miss that poor maniac. May he rest in peace."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=abaddon_note_443
#. This entry is written by Mal Si'ah, who uses they/them or gender-neutral pronouns to refer to themselves.
#. This is only relevant in languages with more than one first-person pronoun.
#. Redacted text:
#. "Argan managed to achieve such unparalleled success with Subject 00-44A. Some say it was a blessing from Uria — others say it was his power as the Master of Darkness."
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:130
msgid ""
"If Yechnagoth’s original soul was able to fully utilize the power of her <b>energy heart</b> after being transplanted to a new body, why could another soul not do the same? Why, <b>contamination</b>, of course! That pesky obstacle is the main thing that stands between us and the ability to create a god. Even now, I fail to comprehend how █████ ███████ to achieve ████ unparalleled ███████ ████ ███████ 00-44A█ Some say ██ ███ █ ████████ ████ ████ — others say it was ███ █████ ██ ███ ██████ ██ ████████. Yet, my analysis never revealed any lingering influence from either of them.\n"
"\n"
"As much as I hate to admit it, last night that arrogant cretin Mal Hekuba suggested a most splendid idea. Contamination is, in essence, the rejection of godhood by lifeforms whose souls were never destined for it. But, what if instead of installing the core unit into a creature that naturally has a soul, we used a non-sentient host alongside an <i>inert</i> donor soul? The energy heart might only need to perceive the <i>presence</i> of a soul, not its <i>agency</i>.\n"
"\n"
"In the past, scholars often argued that things without a soul cannot be considered <i>living</i> creatures, for they have no inherent force to push them towards a certain destiny. Indeed, fully artificial lifeforms like pure Shaxthals do not and <i>cannot</i> fathom their own pitiful existence devoid of purpose other than feeding, breeding, and obeying the <b>will of the hive</b>. Only a decadent civilization like the Argazars could have intentionally come up with such an obscene mockery of life.\n"
"\n"
"In our universe there is no rule forbidding things lacking a soul from being <i>granted</i> one by an external influence. Necromancers throughout the millennia have used this to their advantage, denying themselves passage to Arvadelidrya in exchange for greater power. Whether it be their own rotting bodies, or flashy trinkets pilfered from opulent tyrants, they have proven beyond a doubt that you can graft a soul on pretty much anything that has physical form.\n"
"\n"
"Despite her initial disgust upon finding out who contributed to my proposal, the <b>Fire</b> expressed interest in finding out how we could use this as a basis for the development of a new class of weaponry. I am disappointed to see Argan’s protégée indulge in this primitive way of thinking, but if it is what it takes to give the Thornfire program a new lease on life, then so be it.\n"
"\n"
"I am sorry, Argan, but neither you nor I were ever the kind to turn our backs on inspiration whenever it struck. Plus, would it not be the greatest irony of all if an innately <b>soulless</b> creature were to attain apotheosis?"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E2S11_memo_104
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:149
msgid "Memo #104: codename ‘Ivyel’"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E2S11_memo_104
#. This entry is written by Mal Si'ah... you know the drill.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:153
msgid ""
"Per the Fire of Uria’s command, work on the Ivyel program is to continue at Telchior’s Hold Underground Facility.\n"
"\n"
"Biomechanical Infiltrator Unit 01 and a Mark 4 ThC assembly have already been delivered at the time of this writing.\n"
"\n"
"The following assets will be delivered within the next 2 days:\n"
"\n"
" • 1x MTAL-03 core\n"
" • 1x EME serial I0508 “Ivyel”\n"
" • 1x Type-C equipment frame\n"
" • 1x Biological sample 90372-A “Elynia-Thanadria”\n"
"\n"
"Project management has been delegated to Iron Council member Mal Hekuba, who shall oversee all tasks going forward.\n"
"\n"
"An engineering team led by Mal Si’ah and Mal Vrel’leru of the Order of Dreadcrafters is scheduled to arrive within 14 days for on-site work.\n"
"\n"
"Signed off by: Mal Kendria, Iron Council"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E2S11_note_2
#. This entry is written by Mal Si'ah... you know the drill.
#. When he says "the girl's construction", he is referring to the manner
#. in which Elyssa's body was constructed.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:179
msgid ""
"A scientist such as I hardly has the time to entertain the delusions of zealots who desperately seek after theophanic experiences to give their pitiful lives some semblance of purpose. And yet, here I am, aiding that decrepit pile of bones once again.\n"
"\n"
"Truth be told, for a very long time I have had a bad feeling about him and the grudge he holds against the Fire. He has gone as far as to try prying information off me about the girl’s construction, no doubt in the hope of finding weaknesses for him to exploit.\n"
"\n"
"While I normally pride myself in my neutrality in matters of interpersonal conflict amongst the upper echelons, I cannot help but regard the Fire with a certain fondness and loyalty; after all, I am the only Dreadcrafter that has ever been entrusted with her body’s upkeep, and she remains Argan’s sole living legacy. I am sure my uncooperativeness has earned me Mal Hekuba’s scorn, but both he and I know too well that my continued existence is crucial for his lofty pursuits to have the slightest chance of yielding fruit.\n"
"\n"
"Should he somehow succeed in attaining godhood, I surmise I am going to become one of his first targets. Mayhap his inevitable attempt to plunder all the information I have accrued throughout the ages will cause his feeble mind to implode.\n"
"\n"
"Oh, Argan, would that you were here to keep the children in check. I fear your absence is about to be felt even harder by all."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E2S11_note_3
#. This entry is written by Mal Si'ah... you know the drill.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:196
msgid ""
"This creature, this... ‘Ivyel’. Even in the early days, it has exhibited an unusual degree of sentience despite Mal Kendria’s extensive work on conditioning the donor soul. Is it because of that spectacularly rushed initial deployment? Unlike the Abaddon specimen, contamination remains within the nominal range, so it is impossible to tell if the soul is manifesting or not.\n"
"\n"
"It has taken quite well to being outfitted with the completed type-C equipment, almost as if it actively <i>wants</i> to become Elynia-Thanadria. One possibility is that it has enough self-awareness that it perceives mimicry as an escape from its dead-ended existence. Another possibility is that the donor soul is manifesting, and they knew the erstwhile Lady of Light and regarded her as some form of salvation; Mal Zilchis is not into the habit of recording the origin of the donors, so I fear I may never be able to verify this unless the creature speaks up and confirms my theory itself— herself?\n"
"\n"
"Side note: This is such a novel situation, I find it hard to decide how I should address ‘Ivyel’. She has a certain preference for being referred to as ‘she’, and ‘Elynia’, but that name is far too problematic around these parts and is best used only while in the elves’ presence; after all, the last thing we need is for everyone to panic thinking the real deal has decided to appear out of nowhere."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:209
msgid "The Day of the Longest Night"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:212
msgid ""
"On the day of the Longest Night, the New Guardian of Darkness shall rise from beyond to claim her rightful place amongst the Guardians of the Second Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"On that day, the New Guardian of Life shall rise again, more powerful than before.\n"
"\n"
"That is the day we have lived for.\n"
"\n"
"The day that shall bring upon our doomed existence the promise of a new beginning."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_urvatha
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:223
msgid "Urvatha"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_urvatha
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:226
msgid ""
"Originally a peaceful world not predestined to harbor civilization, Urvatha was chosen by Iluvia as one of the destinations for the survivors of the First Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"Over time, the lack of a guardian who could guide them resulted in devastating and long-lasting wars over increasingly scarce resources — thus earning it a new name for outsiders and natives alike: <b>‘Inferno’</b>.\n"
"\n"
"While Urvatha continues to be largely heterogeneous, its most inhospitable regions are much better known in Irdyan lore than the rest.\n"
"\n"
"Despite originally lacking a guardian and a seed, Urvatha has become the domain of the New Guardian of Life."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_silida
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:237
msgid "Silida"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_silida
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:240
msgid ""
"Originally a barren world not predestined to sustain life, Silida was chosen by Iluvia as one of the destinations for the survivors of the First Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that before being erased from existence, the Guardians of Life and Existence adapted this lifeless world as a new home for their peoples. However, their task was left unfinished, and the new inhabitants of the world died out after a few generations. Only many eons later would Silida be populated again by faerie creatures.\n"
"\n"
"Despite originally lacking a guardian and a seed, Silida has become the domain of the New Guardian of Earth."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:249
msgid "On Corruption"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:252
msgid "The First Gods created us and the reality we live in with the intent that our own Original Ten would protect and rule over their creation, and eventually replace their forefathers entirely. Little did they know of the many trials they would face during the First Cycle, and the betrayal that would result in the abrupt end of their own existence."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:254
msgid "Little did they know that the same corruptive force that ravaged their universe would manipulate the order of events to ensure an entryway through the Tree of Life itself."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:256
msgid "It would ensure that the souls of our ten demon gods would be connected directly to the Tree through their very hearts. And then it would corrupt the Tree, and its Protector."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:261
msgid "On Existence"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:264
msgid "The First Gods no longer exist, and now the Tree is completely unguarded. Our universe and our guardians will fail to accomplish their intended mission. Not even Delethia could see this until the First Cycle was over. The songs of our own Ten will never be uttered within the boundaries of our existence, and the wound on the Tree will never be healed."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:266
msgid "Even at the last moment, Delethia could not fully control the final outcome; however, her greatly increased foresight and power after defeating Yarae did allow her to alter it to a limited extent."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:268
msgid "Our lives were carefully arranged before she sacrificed her own to create the Gatekeepers. She entrusted Uria and Xia’el with the devices necessary to put her secret plan into motion. The Second Cycle began."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S7A.1_note2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:270
msgid "At the end, only Four will prevail."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=the_ten_guardians
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:285
msgid "The Ten Guardians"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_life
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:337
msgid "Aspects: Life"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_life
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:340
msgid ""
"The aspect of <b>Life</b> deals primarily with the creation and sustainment of life, as well as the very essence of being in all of its manifestations.\n"
"\n"
"All non-faerie human and human-like creatures were created in the image of the first <b>Guardian of Life</b>, who governed over <b>Ethea</b> during the First Cycle. This incarnation of <b>Uria</b> would prove essential for defeating the corrupted <b>Yarae</b> by using her great might to vanqiush his allies one by one, at the cost of countless innocent lives.\n"
"\n"
"Her next incarnation came into existence on a world other than Ethea due to unknown reasons."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_earth
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:349
msgid "Aspects: Earth"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_earth
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:352
msgid ""
"The aspect of <b>Earth</b> is one of four aspects which directly support Life, paving the way for creation.\n"
"\n"
"All faeriekind creatures were created in the image of the first <b>Guardian of Earth</b>, who was tasked with ruling over <b>Irdya</b> during the First Cycle.\n"
"\n"
"Some myths claim that faeriekind beings were fully incorporeal until after the ascension of the first incarnation of <b>Xia’el</b>, a woman said to have been created out of golden dust by <b>Yarae</b> himself. The god fell in love with his own creation, and desperately wanted her affection; the goddess, however, did not reciprocate, spending the days instead lamenting her subjects’ inability to fully bask in the wonders of the physical realm. As a favor, Yarae granted them physical bodies made from the same fine dust.\n"
"\n"
"Her next incarnation came into existence on a world other than Irdya due to unknown reasons."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:363
msgid "Aspects: Darkness"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:367
msgid ""
"Unlike the majority of the aspects constituting reality, Darkness and Light are derived from the nature of the First Gods themselves, stemming from Existence, and connected to Life in a structural role.\n"
"\n"
"Just like Darkness precedes and succeeds Light from a physical standpoint, it also deals with matters of the mind, whereas Light deals with the soul of every being born under the Tree of Life. However, just as both aspects complement each other, they may also exchange places according to the circumstances.\n"
"\n"
"Merthiaal, the Guardian of Darkness on Yrathid, was the last guardian to be born during the First Cycle, and at the same time, she was the first guardian to perish. Although Yarae’s conflict had not yet begun, he did have an indirect role in causing Merthiaal’s downfall. The young guardian’s emotions clouded her reason; jealousy consumed her heart from inside as she watched her creator’s predilection for her sisters Uria and Xia’el.\n"
"\n"
"In a desperate attempt to prove her worth to Yarae and even surpass his own power, the girl subverted her world’s seed and tried to absorb its energy for herself. Alas, even though their blood was always one and the same, the guardian and the Seed of Darkness were never meant to become one.\n"
"\n"
"Not having learned her own song beforehand, Merthiaal could not assume full control of her new powers. Instead of becoming the true goddess she desired to be, the very aspect she controlled was destroyed — her mind succumbed to insanity as her horrifying new body absorbed the souls of each and every one of her fellow Yrathidians.\n"
"\n"
"Uria put an end to Merthiaal’s rampage by ripping her heart out, destroying her body, and sealing her self in the hope that Yarae could do something to remedy the situation. However, Yarae was offended by the proposition; he refused to help with the resurrection and healing, choosing instead to preserve the lifeless world intact as a testament to his child’s hubris.\n"
"\n"
"That incarnation of Uria would never be able to bring Merthiaal back to life, and the Guardian of Darkness would come to be known as the Eater of Souls, the antithesis of the Guardian of Light. Now lacking a distinct seed, Yrathid would not be restored at the end of the First Cycle, remaining instead a graveyard world per Yarae’s wishes."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S8B_prophecy1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:384
msgid "Lost Prophecy"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=E3S8B_prophecy1
#. Line 1: the ‘Four’ are individuals of indeterminate genders.
#. Line 2: except for the ‘Four’, these names refer to inanimate objects.
#. Line 3: these names also refer to inanimate objects.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:390
msgid ""
"The Infertile Mother shall give birth to Four.\n"
"\n"
"These Four shall seek shelter in the Second. The First shall be consumed, the Tree shall be infected.\n"
"\n"
"The missing Fifth shall provide knowledge. The Eleventh and the Twelfth shall provide hope."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness_and_light
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:399
msgid "Aspects: Darkness and Light"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_darkness_and_light
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:402
msgid "The Aspects of Darkness and Light are both interwoven in the very fabric of our reality. Although the powers they confer are often underestimated on their own, the combination of either aspect with any other can have formidable effects. It is generally agreed that the combination of Darkness and Light in particular serves as a connection to the power of the Union — a power most intimately related to Creation itself."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_pairs
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:407
msgid "Aspects: Pairs"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_pairs
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:410
msgid ""
"Life draws from Light and Darknesss, Existence draws from Darkness and Light. Fire and Water oppose each other just as Creation and Destruction do. Thunder and Ice are opposites in the same sense as Earth and Air complement each other.\n"
"\n"
"All the aspects that govern our universe are closely related and equally important to the continuance of reality. Their roles are as flexible as necessary to accomplish the ultimate goal of preserving the First Gods’ legacy, no matter the cost."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_knowledge
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:417
msgid "Aspects: Knowledge"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=aspect_info_knowledge
#. “To brook” below is used in an obsolete sense; namely
#. “to use/enjoy/have the full employment of” (from wiktionary).
#. It also serves as a pun.
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:423
msgid ""
"Fire forges knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Light wards knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Darkness craves knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Water brooks knowledge."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_energy_heart
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:434
msgid "On the Energy Heart"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_energy_heart
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:437
msgid ""
"Guardian-class beings are distinguished by the existence of a special organ in their bodies called the Energy Heart. The organ acts as a virtuallly unlimited source of energy and sustenance for the creature, able to keep it alive under circumstances that would otherwise result in permanent damage or even death. In fact, the host body can suffer any kind of injuries and they will be gradually healed by the Energy Heart, the healing rate depending on the severity of the damage as well as the host’s contamination level.\n"
"\n"
"The organ goes through its own growth and maturation process independent from the host body. Norsulan studies conducted on the Seed of Fire during the Second Cycle have shown that it is possible to artificially grow the organ in the bodies of non-Guardians, albeit with disastrous effects. An alternative approach was used to build the first prototype of an artificial Guardian, keeping the Energy Heart in a separate insulated container with a direct pathway to the host’s nervous system, and an electronic control unit.\n"
"\n"
"The research subjects were all deceased Norsulans, and none of them managed to establish a stable connection with their Energy Hearts. It is suspected that there is a less evident connection between the body, Energy Heart, and spirit of a real Guardian that allows them to fully control their three constituent parts — a connection to the seed that gave them birth, and the Greater Design laid out first by Yarae, and then by Delethia."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_union
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:446
msgid "On the Union"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=tech_union
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:449
msgid ""
"The Orbs of Light and Darkness do not just allow those blessed by Iluvia to summon the Union itself. Given every aspect’s individual affiliation with either path, it may be possible to use the Orbs as instruments to tap into the powers of the other aspects.\n"
"\n"
"As the first Avatar of the Union herself, Iluvia made use of this mechanism to aid Uria and Xia’el in destroying every other corrupted guardian before banishing Yarae from our universe."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_argan_1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:459
msgid ""
"<i>(This entry has Argan’s name attached to it.)</i>\n"
"\n"
"Her mission as the Guardian of Life of our cycle was subverted through a series of unfortunate circumstances, but it is quite inaccurate to claim that she only ever destroys life.\n"
"\n"
"Certainly, countless lives on both Urvatha and Irdya have been felled by her hands or those of her subordinates, but she has also <i>created</i> life in her pursuit of power by adapting the creations of Norsula and the Argazar civilization.\n"
"\n"
"The scriptures say that the Guardian of Life should not be able to create life, only guard it; her achievements in this regard only prove beyond a doubt that she is worthy of becoming the god who shall guide us to paradise."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_argan_2
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:473
msgid ""
"<i>(This entry has Argan’s name attached to it.)</i>\n"
"\n"
"The fact that the Norsulans have access to in-depth knowledge of the guardians’ biology has been quite useful to Uria thus far, but she knows this will become a double-edged sword very soon.\n"
"\n"
"Even more worrying yet is the Seer’s prophecy: “the new Guardian of Water will rise once more and attempt to rob the Guardian of Life of her rightful prize”. Although Uria has agents on Norsula trying to locate this man—or beast—before his awakening can take place, it is a foolish endeavor to attempt preventing events foretold by the Seer. Elyssa and I know this too well."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_argan_3
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:485
msgid ""
"<i>(This entry has Argan’s name attached to it.)</i>\n"
"\n"
"Around the time I first arrived on Irdya, Norsulans were still a largely ignorant bunch, their knowledge of magic majorly lacking compared to the Irdyans, and their mastery of the worldly sciences barely meeting expectations when measured against the Etheans.\n"
"\n"
"And yet, now that I finally make contact with “my” people again, I find out everything has drastically changed. Their magic still pales in comparison to the world-transforming feats performed by the likes of Wesnoth or their predecessors, yet they have built a technological paradise amidst a universe plagued by stagnation; their advancements now eclipse those of Ethea. Some claim that an external influence contributed to their massively accelerated evolution.\n"
"\n"
"My memories have become too hazy after millennia of stumbling around, but I recall feeling some kind of attachment to that world before meeting Elynia, despite their intolerance for my endeavors; I could swear there even was a person who was very precious to me. I wish I could remember."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=e3s12_elyssa_1
#: After_the_Storm/journey/world.cfg:499
msgid ""
"<i>(This entry has Elyssa’s name attached to it but lacks an actual title. It seems much more recent than the other entries.)</i>\n"
"\n"
"Just as Norsula’s technological advancements were without a doubt the consequence of external meddling, much of Ethea’s own over the past few centuries were meticulously orchestrated by Norsulan agents. To her credit, the previous Norsulan empress clearly only wanted to share her people’s boon with the Etheans, perhaps in the hope of securing a new stable trading partner, nothing else.\n"
"\n"
"However, I’m not so sure about the new regime’s intentions. Their decision to reveal Norsula’s existence right at the end of Ethea’s most devastating war yet seems far too convenient, too much of a coincidence.\n"
"\n"
"Valdir’s successor... Uria is right to have misgivings about him; his decision to secure the Seed of Life is confirmation enough that he has an agenda of his own. Sadly, we have never been able to infiltrate his close circles. It truly makes me wonder... have he and his precessors been intentionally drip-feeding us information so we would get to this point?\n"
"\n"
"The Seer’s ramblings on the matter get hazier and more confusing the closer we get to that pivotal moment, starting from the Day of the Longest Night on Irdya. The only thing we know for sure is that she will eventually be slain—not sure by who—at which point there is no more information she can provide since her vision is bound by her mortal existence."
msgstr ""

